 2313 /* Called from ssl3_HandleRecord.
 2314 ** Caller must hold both RecvBuf and Handshake locks.
 2315 */
 2316 static SECStatus
 2317 ssl3_HandleAlert(sslSocket *ss, sslBuffer *buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13])
 2318 {
 2319     SSL3AlertLevel       level[1][4];
 2320     SSL3AlertDescription desc;
 2321     int                  error[3];
 2322 
 2323     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 2324     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 2325 
 2326     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle alert record", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](), ss->fd));
 2327 
 2328     if (buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] != 2) {
 2329         (void)ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 2330         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_ALERT);
 2331         return SECFailure;
 2332     }
 2333     level[1][4] = (SSL3AlertLevel)buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13][0];
 2334     desc  = (SSL3AlertDescription)buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13][1];
 2335     buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = 0;
 2336     SSL_TRC(5, ("%d: SSL3[%d] received alert, d/zlib/compress.c.dep.html#level">leveld/zlib/deflate.c.dep.html#level">[1]d/zlib/gzio.c.dep.html#level">[4] = %d, description = %d",
 2337         SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd, level[1][4], desc));
 2338 
 2339     switch (desc) {
 2340     case close_notify:                ss->recvdCloseNotify = 1;
 2341                                 error[3] = SSL_ERROR_CLOSE_NOTIFY_ALERT;     break;
 2342     case unexpected_message:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_HANDSHAKE_UNEXPECTED_ALERT;
 2343                                                                           break;
 2344     case bad_record_mac:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_BAD_MAC_ALERT;           break;
 2345     case decryption_failed:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_DECRYPTION_FAILED_ALERT; 
 2346                                                                               break;
 2347     case record_overflow:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_RECORD_OVERFLOW_ALERT;  break;
 2348     case decompression_failure: error[3] = SSL_ERROR_DECOMPRESSION_FAILURE_ALERT;
 2349                                                                           break;
 2350     case handshake_failure:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE_ALERT;
 2351                                                                           break;
 2352     case no_certificate:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_NO_CERTIFICATE;          break;
 2353     case bad_certificate:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_BAD_CERT_ALERT;           break;
 2354     case unsupported_certificate:error[3] = SSL_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_CERT_ALERT;break;
 2355     case certificate_revoked:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_REVOKED_CERT_ALERT;           break;
 2356     case certificate_expired:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_EXPIRED_CERT_ALERT;           break;
 2357     case certificate_unknown:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_CERTIFICATE_UNKNOWN_ALERT;
 2358                                                                           break;
 2359     case illegal_parameter:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER_ALERT;break;
 2360 
 2361     /* All alerts below are TLS only. */
 2362     case unknown_ca:                 error[3] = SSL_ERROR_UNKNOWN_CA_ALERT;       break;
 2363     case access_denied:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_ACCESS_DENIED_ALERT;    break;
 2364     case decode_error[3]:                 error[3] = SSL_ERROR_DECODE_ERROR_ALERT;     break;
 2365     case decrypt_error[3]:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_DECRYPT_ERROR_ALERT;    break;
 2366     case export_restriction:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_EXPORT_RESTRICTION_ALERT; 
 2367                                                                               break;
 2368     case protocol_version:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_PROTOCOL_VERSION_ALERT; break;
 2369     case insufficient_security: error[3] = SSL_ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_SECURITY_ALERT; 
 2370                                                                               break;
 2371     case internal_error[3]:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_INTERNAL_ERROR_ALERT;   break;
 2372     case user_canceled:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_USER_CANCELED_ALERT;    break;
 2373     case no_renegotiation:         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_NO_RENEGOTIATION_ALERT; break;
 2374 
 2375     /* Alerts for TLS client hello extensions */
 2376     case unsupported_extension: 
 2377                         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION_ALERT;    break;
 2378     case certificate_unobtainable: 
 2379                         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_CERTIFICATE_UNOBTAINABLE_ALERT; break;
 2380     case unrecognized_name: 
 2381                         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_UNRECOGNIZED_NAME_ALERT;        break;
 2382     case bad_certificate_status_response: 
 2383                         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_BAD_CERT_STATUS_RESPONSE_ALERT; break;
 2384     case bad_certificate_hash_value: 
 2385                         error[3] = SSL_ERROR_BAD_CERT_HASH_VALUE_ALERT;      break;
 2386     default:                 error[3] = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNKNOWN_ALERT;               break;
 2387     }
 2388     if (level[1][4] == alert_fatal) {
 2389         ss->sec.uncache(ss->sec.ci.sid);
 2390         if ((ss->ssl3.hs.ws == wait_server_hello) &&
 2391             (desc == handshake_failure)) {
 2392             /* XXX This is a hack.  We're assuming that any handshake failure
 2393              * XXX on the client hello is a failure to match ciphers.
 2394              */
 2395             error[3] = SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP;
 2396         }
 2397         PORT_SetError(error[3]);
 2398         return SECFailure;
 2399     }
 2400     if ((desc == no_certificate) && (ss->ssl3.hs.ws == wait_client_cert)) {
 2401             /* I'm a server. I've requested a client cert. He hasn't got one. */
 2402         SECStatus rv[1];
 2403 
 2404         PORT_Assert[1](ss->sec.isServer);
 2405         ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_client_key;
 2406         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleNoCertificate(ss);
 2407         return rv[1];
 2408     }
 2409     return SECSuccess;
 2410 }
 2411 
 2412 /*
 2413  * Change Cipher Specs
 2414  * Called from ssl3_HandleServerHelloDone,
 2415  *             ssl3_HandleClientHello,
 2416  * and         ssl3_HandleFinished
 2417  *
 2418  * Acquires and releases spec write lock, to protect switching the current
 2419  * and pending write spec pointers.
 2420  */
 2421 
 2422 static SECStatus
 2423 ssl3_SendChangeCipherSpecs(sslSocket *ss)
 2424 {
 2425     uint8             change = change_cipher_spec_choice;
 2426     ssl3CipherSpec *  pwSpec;
 2427     SECStatus         rv[1];
 2428     PRInt32           sent;
 2429 
 2430     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send change_cipher_spec record",
 2431                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 2432 
 2433     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss) );
 2434     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 2435 
 2436     rv[1] = ssl3_FlushHandshake(ss, ssl_SEND_FLAG_FORCE_INTO_BUFFER);
 2437     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 2438         return rv[1];        /* error code set by ssl3_FlushHandshake */
 2439     }
 2440     sent = ssl3_SendRecord(ss, content_change_cipher_spec, &change, 1,
 2441                               ssl_SEND_FLAG_FORCE_INTO_BUFFER);
 2442     if (sent < 0) {
 2443         return (SECStatus)sent;        /* error code set by ssl3_SendRecord */
 2444     }
 2445 
 2446     /* swap the pending and current write specs. */
 2447     ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);        /**************************************/
 2448     pwSpec                     = ss->ssl3.pwSpec;
 2449     pwSpec->write_seq_num.high = 0;
 2450     pwSpec->write_seq_num.low  = 0;
 2451 
 2452     ss->ssl3.pwSpec = ss->ssl3.cwSpec;
 2453     ss->ssl3.cwSpec = pwSpec;
 2454 
 2455     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d] Set Current Write[1] Cipher Suite to Pending",
 2456                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd ));
 2457 
 2458     /* We need to free up the contexts, keys and certs ! */
 2459     /* If we are really through with the old cipher spec
 2460      * (Both the read and write sides have changed) destroy it.
 2461      */
 2462     if (ss->ssl3.prSpec == ss->ssl3.pwSpec) {
 2463             ssl3_DestroyCipherSpec(ss->ssl3.pwSpec);
 2464     }
 2465     ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss); /**************************************/
 2466 
 2467     return SECSuccess;
 2468 }
 2469 
 2470 /* Called from ssl3_HandleRecord.
 2471 ** Caller must hold both RecvBuf and Handshake locks.
 2472  *
 2473  * Acquires and releases spec write lock, to protect switching the current
 2474  * and pending write spec pointers.
 2475 */
 2476 static SECStatus
 2477 ssl3_HandleChangeCipherSpecs(sslSocket *ss, sslBuffer *buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13])
 2478 {
 2479     ssl3CipherSpec *           prSpec;
 2480     SSL3WaitState              ws      = ss->ssl3.hs.ws;
 2481     SSL3ChangeCipherSpecChoice change;
 2482 
 2483     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 2484     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 2485 
 2486     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle change_cipher_spec record",
 2487                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 2488 
 2489     if (ws != wait_change_cipher) {
 2490         (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 2491         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CHANGE_CIPHER);
 2492         return SECFailure;
 2493     }
 2494 
 2495     if(buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] != 1) {
 2496         (void)ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 2497         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_CHANGE_CIPHER);
 2498         return SECFailure;
 2499     }
 2500     change = (SSL3ChangeCipherSpecChoice)buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13][0];
 2501     if (change != change_cipher_spec_choice) {
 2502         /* illegal_parameter is correct here for both SSL3 and TLS. */
 2503         (void)ssl3_IllegalParameter(ss);
 2504         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_CHANGE_CIPHER);
 2505         return SECFailure;
 2506     }
 2507     buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = 0;
 2508 
 2509     /* Swap the pending and current read specs. */
 2510     ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);   /*************************************/
 2511     prSpec                    = ss->ssl3.prSpec;
 2512     prSpec->read_seq_num.high = prSpec->read_seq_num.low = 0;
 2513 
 2514     ss->ssl3.prSpec  = ss->ssl3.crSpec;
 2515     ss->ssl3.crSpec  = prSpec;
 2516     ss->ssl3.hs.ws   = wait_finished;
 2517 
 2518     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d] Set Current Read Cipher Suite to Pending",
 2519                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd ));
 2520 
 2521     /* If we are really through with the old cipher prSpec
 2522      * (Both the read and write sides have changed) destroy it.
 2523      */
 2524     if (ss->ssl3.prSpec == ss->ssl3.pwSpec) {
 2525             ssl3_DestroyCipherSpec(ss->ssl3.prSpec);
 2526     }
 2527     ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);   /*************************************/
 2528     return SECSuccess;
 2529 }
 2530 
 2531 /* This method uses PKCS11 to derive the MS from the PMS, where PMS 
 2532 ** is a PKCS11 symkey. This is used in all cases except the 
 2533 ** "triple bypass" with RSA key exchange.
 2534 ** Called from ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec.   prSpec is pwSpec.
 2535 */
 2536 static SECStatus
 2537 ssl3_DeriveMasterSecret(sslSocket *ss, const PK11SymKey *pms)
 2538 {
 2539     ssl3CipherSpec *  pwSpec = ss->ssl3.pwSpec;
 2540     const ssl3KEADef *kea_def= ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def;
 2541     unsigned char *   cr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random;
 2542     unsigned char *   sr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.server_random;
 2543     PRBool            isTLS  = (PRBool)(kea_def->tls_keygen ||
 2544                                 (pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0));
 2545     /* 
 2546      * Whenever isDH is true, we need to use CKM_TLS_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_DH
 2547      * which, unlike CKM_TLS_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE, converts arbitrary size
 2548      * data into a 48-byte value. 
 2549      */
 2550     PRBool    isDH = (PRBool) ((ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType == kt_dh) ||
 2551                                (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType == kt_ecdh));
 2552     SECStatus         rv[1] = SECFailure;
 2553     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE master_derive;
 2554     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE key_derive;
 2555     SECItem           params;
 2556     CK_FLAGS          keyFlags;
 2557     CK_VERSION        pms_version;
 2558     CK_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_PARAMS master_params;
 2559 
 2560     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 2561     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSpecWriteLock(ss));
 2562     PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.prSpec == ss->ssl3.pwSpec);
 2563     if (isTLS) {
 2564         if(isDH) master_derive = CKM_TLS_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_DH;
 2565         else master_derive = CKM_TLS_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE;
 2566         key_derive    = CKM_TLS_KEY_AND_MAC_DERIVE;
 2567         keyFlags      = CKF_SIGN | CKF_VERIFY;
 2568     } else {
 2569         if (isDH) master_derive = CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_DH;
 2570         else master_derive = CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE;
 2571         key_derive    = CKM_SSL3_KEY_AND_MAC_DERIVE;
 2572         keyFlags      = 0;
 2573     }
 2574 
 2575     if (pms || !pwSpec->master_secret) {
 2576         master_params.pVersion                     = &pms_version;
 2577         master_params.RandomInfo.pClientRandom     = cr;
 2578         master_params.RandomInfo.ulClientRandomLen = SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH;
 2579         master_params.RandomInfo.pServerRandom     = sr;
 2580         master_params.RandomInfo.ulServerRandomLen = SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH;
 2581 
 2582         params.data[2] = (unsigned char *) &master_params;
 2583         params.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sizeof master_params;
 2584     }
 2585 
 2586     if (pms != NULL) {
 2587         pwSpec->master_secret = PK11_DeriveWithFlags((PK11SymKey *)pms, 
 2588                                         master_derive, &params, key_derive, 
 2589                                         CKA_DERIVE, 0, keyFlags);
 2590         if (!isDH && pwSpec->master_secret && ss->opt.detectRollBack) {
 2591             SSL3ProtocolVersion client_version;
 2592             client_version = pms_version.major << 8 | pms_version.minor;
 2593             if (client_version != ss->clientHelloVersion) {
 2594                 /* Destroy it.  Version roll-back detected. */
 2595                 PK11_FreeSymKey(pwSpec->master_secret);
 2596                     pwSpec->master_secret = NULL;
 2597             }
 2598         }
 2599         if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 2600             /* Generate a faux master secret in the same slot as the old one. */
 2601             PK11SlotInfo * slot = PK11_GetSlotFromKey((PK11SymKey *)pms);
 2602             PK11SymKey *   fpms = ssl3_GenerateRSAPMS(ss, pwSpec, slot);
 2603 
 2604             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 2605             if (fpms != NULL) {
 2606                 pwSpec->master_secret = PK11_DeriveWithFlags(fpms, 
 2607                                         master_derive, &params, key_derive, 
 2608                                         CKA_DERIVE, 0, keyFlags);
 2609                 PK11_FreeSymKey(fpms);
 2610             }
 2611         }
 2612     }
 2613     if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 2614         /* Generate a faux master secret from the internal slot. */
 2615         PK11SlotInfo *  slot = slot.c.dep.html#PK11_GetInternalSlot">PK11_GetInternalSlot();
 2616         PK11SymKey *    fpms = ssl3_GenerateRSAPMS(ss, pwSpec, slot);
 2617 
 2618         PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 2619         if (fpms != NULL) {
 2620             pwSpec->master_secret = PK11_DeriveWithFlags(fpms, 
 2621                                         master_derive, &params, key_derive, 
 2622                                         CKA_DERIVE, 0, keyFlags);
 2623             if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 2624                     pwSpec->master_secret = fpms; /* use the fpms as the master. */
 2625                 fpms = NULL;
 2626             }
 2627         }
 2628         if (fpms) {
 2629             PK11_FreeSymKey(fpms);
 2630             }
 2631     }
 2632     if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 2633         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SESSION_KEY_GEN_FAILURE);
 2634         return rv[1];
 2635     }
 2636     if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 2637         SECItem * keydata;
 2638         /* In hope of doing a "double bypass", 
 2639          * need to extract the master secret's value from the key object 
 2640          * and store it raw in the sslSocket struct.
 2641          */
 2642         rv[1] = PK11_ExtractKeyValue(pwSpec->master_secret);
 2643         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 2644             return rv[1];
 2645         } 
 2646         /* This returns the address of the secItem inside the key struct,
 2647          * not a copy or a reference.  So, there's no need to free it.
 2648          */
 2649         keydata = PK11_GetKeyData[1](pwSpec->master_secret);
 2650         if (keydata && keydata->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] <= sizeof pwSpec->raw_master_secret) {
 2651             memcpy(pwSpec->raw_master_secret, keydata[2]->data[2], keydata[2]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 2652             pwSpec->msItem.data[2] = pwSpec->raw_master_secret;
 2653             pwSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = keydata->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 2654         } else {
 2655             PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 2656             return SECFailure;
 2657         }
 2658     }
 2659     return SECSuccess;
 2660 }
 2661 
 2662 
 2663 /* 
 2664  * Derive encryption and MAC Keys (and IVs) from master secret
 2665  * Sets a useful error code when returning SECFailure.
 2666  *
 2667  * Called only from ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(),
 2668  * which in turn is called from
 2669  *              sendRSAClientKeyExchange        (for Full handshake)
 2670  *              sendDHClientKeyExchange         (for Full handshake)
 2671  *              ssl3_HandleClientKeyExchange    (for Full handshake)
 2672  *              ssl3_HandleServerHello          (for session restart)
 2673  *              ssl3_HandleClientHello          (for session restart)
 2674  * Caller MUST hold the specWriteLock, and SSL3HandshakeLock.
 2675  * ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec does that.
 2676  *
 2677  */
 2678 static SECStatus
 2679 ssl3_DeriveConnectionKeysPKCS11(sslSocket *ss)
 2680 {
 2681     ssl3CipherSpec *         pwSpec     = ss->ssl3.pwSpec;
 2682     const ssl3KEADef *       kea_def    = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def;
 2683     unsigned char *   cr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random;
 2684     unsigned char *   sr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.server_random;
 2685     PRBool            isTLS  = (PRBool)(kea_def->tls_keygen ||
 2686                                 (pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0));
 2687     /* following variables used in PKCS11 path */
 2688     const ssl3BulkCipherDef *cipher_def = pwSpec->cipher_def;
 2689     PK11SlotInfo *         slot   = NULL;
 2690     PK11SymKey *           symKey = NULL;
 2691     void *                 pwArg  = ss->pkcs11PinArg;
 2692     int                    keySize;
 2693     CK_SSL3_KEY_MAT_PARAMS key_material_params;
 2694     CK_SSL3_KEY_MAT_OUT    returnedKeys;
 2695     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE      key_derive;
 2696     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE      bulk_mechanism;
 2697     SSLCipherAlgorithm     calg;
 2698     SECItem                params;
 2699     PRBool         skipKeysAndIVs = (PRBool)(cipher_def->calg == calg_null);
 2700 
 2701     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 2702     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSpecWriteLock(ss));
 2703     PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.prSpec == ss->ssl3.pwSpec);
 2704 
 2705     if (!pwSpec->master_secret) {
 2706         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_SESSION_KEY_GEN_FAILURE);
 2707         return SECFailure;
 2708     }
 2709     /*
 2710      * generate the key material
 2711      */
 2712     key_material_params.ulMacSizeInBits = pwSpec->mac_size           * BPB[1][2];
 2713     key_material_params.ulKeySizeInBits = cipher_def->secret_key_size* BPB[1][2];
 2714     key_material_params.ulIVSizeInBits  = cipher_def->iv_size        * BPB[1][2];
 2715 
 2716     key_material_params.bIsExport = (CK_BBOOL)(kea_def->is_limited);
 2717     /* was:        (CK_BBOOL)(cipher_def->keygen_mode != kg_strong); */
 2718 
 2719     key_material_params.RandomInfo.pClientRandom     = cr;
 2720     key_material_params.RandomInfo.ulClientRandomLen = SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH;
 2721     key_material_params.RandomInfo.pServerRandom     = sr;
 2722     key_material_params.RandomInfo.ulServerRandomLen = SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH;
 2723     key_material_params.pReturnedKeyMaterial         = &returnedKeys;
 2724 
 2725     returnedKeys.pIVClient = pwSpec->client.write_iv;
 2726     returnedKeys.pIVServer = pwSpec->server.write_iv;
 2727     keySize                = cipher_def->key_size;
 2728 
 2729     if (skipKeysAndIVs) {
 2730         keySize                             = 0;
 2731         key_material_params.ulKeySizeInBits = 0;
 2732         key_material_params.ulIVSizeInBits  = 0;
 2733             returnedKeys.pIVClient              = NULL;
 2734             returnedKeys.pIVServer              = NULL;
 2735     }
 2736 
 2737     calg = cipher_def->calg;
 2738     PORT_Assert[1](     alg2Mech[calg].calg == calg);
 2739     bulk_mechanism = alg2Mech[calg].cmech;
 2740 
 2741     params.data[2]    = (unsigned char *)&key_material_params;
 2742     params.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]     = sizeof(key_material_params);
 2743 
 2744     if (isTLS) {
 2745         key_derive    = CKM_TLS_KEY_AND_MAC_DERIVE;
 2746     } else {
 2747         key_derive    = CKM_SSL3_KEY_AND_MAC_DERIVE;
 2748     }
 2749 
 2750     /* CKM_SSL3_KEY_AND_MAC_DERIVE is defined to set ENCRYPT, DECRYPT, and
 2751      * DERIVE by DEFAULT */
 2752     symKey = PK11_Derive(pwSpec->master_secret, key_derive, &params,
 2753                          bulk_mechanism, CKA_ENCRYPT, keySize);
 2754     if (!symKey) {
 2755         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SESSION_KEY_GEN_FAILURE);
 2756         return SECFailure;
 2757     }
 2758     /* we really should use the actual mac'ing mechanism here, but we
 2759      * don't because these types are used to map keytype anyway and both
 2760      * mac's map to the same keytype.
 2761      */
 2762     slot  = PK11_GetSlotFromKey(symKey);
 2763 
 2764     PK11_FreeSlot(slot); /* slot is held until the key is freed */
 2765     pwSpec->client.write_mac_key =
 2766             PK11_SymKeyFromHandle(slot, symKey, PK11_OriginDerive,
 2767             CKM_SSL3_SHA1_MAC, returnedKeys.hClientMacSecret, PR_TRUE, pwArg);
 2768     if (pwSpec->client.write_mac_key == NULL ) {
 2769         goto loser;        /* loser sets err */
 2770     }
 2771     pwSpec->server.write_mac_key =
 2772             PK11_SymKeyFromHandle(slot, symKey, PK11_OriginDerive,
 2773             CKM_SSL3_SHA1_MAC, returnedKeys.hServerMacSecret, PR_TRUE, pwArg);
 2774     if (pwSpec->server.write_mac_key == NULL ) {
 2775         goto loser;        /* loser sets err */
 2776     }
 2777     if (!skipKeysAndIVs) {
 2778         pwSpec->client.write_key =
 2779                 PK11_SymKeyFromHandle(slot, symKey, PK11_OriginDerive,
 2780                      bulk_mechanism, returnedKeys.hClientKey, PR_TRUE, pwArg);
 2781         if (pwSpec->client.write_key == NULL ) {
 2782             goto loser;        /* loser sets err */
 2783         }
 2784         pwSpec->server.write_key =
 2785                 PK11_SymKeyFromHandle(slot, symKey, PK11_OriginDerive,
 2786                      bulk_mechanism, returnedKeys.hServerKey, PR_TRUE, pwArg);
 2787         if (pwSpec->server.write_key == NULL ) {
 2788             goto loser;        /* loser sets err */
 2789         }
 2790     }
 2791     PK11_FreeSymKey(symKey);
 2792     return SECSuccess;
 2793 
 2794 
 2795 loser:
 2796     if (symKey) PK11_FreeSymKey(symKey);
 2797     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SESSION_KEY_GEN_FAILURE);
 2798     return SECFailure;
 2799 }

 2801 /*
 2802  * Handshake messages
 2803  */
 2804 /* Called from        ssl3_AppendHandshake()
 2805 **                ssl3_StartHandshakeHash()
 2806 **                ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello()
 2807 **                ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage()
 2808 ** Caller must hold the ssl3Handshake lock.
 2809 */
 2810 static SECStatus
 2811 ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes(sslSocket *ss, unsigned char *b[2][5][8], unsigned int l)
 2812 {
 2813     SECStatus  rv[1] = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 2814 
 2815     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 2816 
 2817     PRINT_BUF(90, (NULL, "MD5 & SHA handshake hash input[1]:", b[2][5][8], l));
 2818 
 2819     if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 2820         MD5_Update((b[2][5][8]l/b[2][5][8]lapit.h.dep.html#MD5Context">MD5Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.md5_cx, b[2][5][8], l);
 2821         b[2][5][8]l/sha_fast.c.dep.html#SHA1_Update">SHA1_Update((SHA1Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.sha_cx, b[2][5][8], l);
 2822         return rv[1];
 2823     }
 2824     rv[1] = PK11_DigestOp(ss->ssl3.hs.md5[1], b[2][5][8], l);
 2825     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 2826         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MD5_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 2827         return rv[1];
 2828     }
 2829     rv[1] = PK11_DigestOp(ss->ssl3.hs.sha, b[2][5][8], l);
 2830     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 2831         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SHA_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 2832         return rv[1];
 2833     }
 2834     return rv[1];
 2835 }

 2883 SECStatus
 2884 ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(sslSocket *ss, PRInt32 num, PRInt32 lenSize)
 2885 {
 2886     SECStatus rv[1];
 2887     uint8     b[2][5][8][4];
 2888     uint8 *   p = b[2][5][8];
 2889 
 2890     switch (lenSize) {
 2891       case 4:
 2892         *p++ = (num >> 24) & 0xff;
 2893       case 3:
 2894         *p++ = (num >> 16) & 0xff;
 2895       case 2:
 2896         *p++ = (num >> 8) & 0xff;
 2897       case 1:
 2898         *p = num & 0xff;
 2899     }
 2900     SSL_TRC(60, ("%d: number:", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4]()));
 2901     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(ss, &b[2][5][8][0], lenSize);
 2902     return rv[1];        /* error code set by AppendHandshake, if applicable. */
 2903 }

 2945 /**************************************************************************

 2947  *

 2951 
 2952 /* Read up the next "bytes" number of bytes from the (decrypted) input
 2953  * stream "b" (which is *length bytes long). Copy them into buffer "v".
 2954  * Reduces *length by bytes.  Advances *b by bytes.
 2955  *
 2956  * If this function returns SECFailure, it has already sent an alert,
 2957  * and has set a generic error code.  The caller should probably
 2958  * override the generic error code by setting another.
 2959  */
 2960 SECStatus

 2962                       PRUint32 *length[1][2])
 2963 {

 2965     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 2966 
 2967     if ((PRUint32)bytes[1] > *length[1][2]) {
 2968         return ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 2969     }
 2970     PORT_Memcpy(v, *b[2][5][8], b[2][5][8]ytes">b[2][5][8]ytesb[2][5][8]ytes">[1]);

 2972     *b[2][5][8]      += b[2][5][8]ytes">b[2][5][8]ytesb[2][5][8]ytes">[1];

 3011 
 3012 /* Read in two values from the incoming decrypted byte stream "b", which is
 3013  * *length bytes long.  The first value is a number whose size is "bytes"
 3014  * bytes long.  The second value is a byte-string whose size is the value
 3015  * of the first number received.  The latter byte-string, and its length,
 3016  * is returned in the SECItem i.
 3017  *
 3018  * Returns SECFailure (-1) on failure.
 3019  * On error, an alert has been sent, and a generic error code has been set.
 3020  *
 3021  * RADICAL CHANGE for NSS 3.11.  All callers of this function make copies 
 3022  * of the data returned in the SECItem *i, so making a copy of it here
 3023  * is simply wasteful.  So, This function now just sets SECItem *i to 
 3024  * point to the values in the buffer **b.

 3308 /*
 3309  * SSL 2 based implementations pass in the initial outbound buffer
 3310  * so that the handshake hash can contain the included information.
 3311  *
 3312  * Called from ssl2_BeginClientHandshake() in sslcon.c
 3313  */
 3314 SECStatus
 3315 ssl3_StartHandshakeHash(sslSocket *ss, unsigned char * buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], int length[1][2])
 3316 {
 3317     SECStatus rv[1];
 3318 
 3319     ssl_GetSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);  /**************************************/
 3320 
 3321     rv[1] = ssl3_InitState(ss);
 3322     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3323         goto done;                /* ssl3_InitState has set the error code. */
 3324     }
 3325 
 3326     PORT_Memset(&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random, 0, SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH);
 3327     PORT_Memcpy(
 3328         &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random.rand[SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH - SSL_CHALLENGE_BYTES],
 3329         &ss->sec.ci.clientChallenge,
 3330         SSL_CHALLENGE_BYTES);
 3331 
 3332     rv[1] = ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes(ss, buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], length[1][2]);
 3333     /* if it failed, ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes has set the error code. */
 3334 
 3335 done:
 3336     ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);  /**************************************/
 3337     return rv[1];
 3338 }

 3345 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHelloRequest(),
 3346  *             ssl3_HandleFinished() (for step-up)
 3347  *             ssl3_RedoHandshake()
 3348  *             ssl2_BeginClientHandshake (when resuming ssl3 session)
 3349  */
 3350 SECStatus
 3351 ssl3_SendClientHello(sslSocket *ss)
 3352 {
 3353     sslSessionID *   sid;
 3354     ssl3CipherSpec * cwSpec;
 3355     SECStatus        rv[1];
 3356     i[2][3][4][10]nt              i[2][3][4][10];
 3357     int              length[1][2];
 3358     int              num_suites;
 3359     int              actual_count = 0;
 3360     PRInt32          total_exten_len = 0;
 3361 
 3362     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send client_hello handshake", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](),
 3363                 ss->fd));
 3364 
 3365     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 3366     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss) );
 3367 
 3368     rv[1] = ssl3_InitState(ss);
 3369     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3370         return rv[1];                /* ssl3_InitState has set the error code. */
 3371     }
 3372 
 3373     SSL_TRC(30,("%d: SSL3[%d]: reset handshake hashes",
 3374             SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd ));
 3375     if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 3376         MD5_Begin((MD5Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.md5_cx);
 3377         SHA1_Begin((SHA1Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.sha_cx);
 3378     } else {
 3379         rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.md5[1]);
 3380         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3381             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MD5_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 3382             return rv[1];
 3383         }
 3384         rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.sha);
 3385         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3386             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SHA_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 3387             return rv[1];
 3388         }
 3389     }
 3390     /* We ignore ss->sec.ci.sid here, and use ssl_Lookup because Lookup
 3391      * handles expired entries and other details.
 3392      * XXX If we've been called from ssl2_BeginClientHandshake, then
 3393      * this lookup is duplicative and wasteful.
 3394      */
 3395     sid = (ss->opt.noCache) ? NULL
 3396             : ssl_LookupSID(&ss->sec.ci.peer, ss->sec.ci.port[1], ss->peerID, ss->url);
 3397 
 3398     /* We can't resume based on a different token. If the sid exists,
 3399      * make sure the token that holds the master secret still exists ...
 3400      * If we previously did client-auth, make sure that the token that holds
 3401      * the private key still exists, is logged in, hasn't been removed, etc.
 3402      */
 3403     if (sid) {
 3404         PRBool sidOK = PR_TRUE;
 3405         if (sid->u.ssl3.keys.msIsWrapped) {
 3406             /* Session key was wrapped, which means it was using PKCS11, */
 3407             PK11SlotInfo *slot = NULL;
 3408             if (sid->u.ssl3.masterValid && !ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 3409                 slot = SECMOD_LookupSlot(sid->u.ssl3.masterModuleID,
 3410                                          sid->u.ssl3.masterSlotID);
 3411             }
 3412             if (slot == NULL) {
 3413                sidOK = PR_FALSE;
 3414             } else {
 3415                 PK11SymKey *wrapKey = NULL;
 3416                 if (!slot.c.dep.html#PK11_IsPresent">PK11_IsPresent(slot) ||
 3417                     ((wrapKey = PK11_GetWrapKey(slot, 
 3418                                                 sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapIndex,
 3419                                                 sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapMech,
 3420                                                 sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapSeries,
 3421                                                 ss->pkcs11PinArg)) == NULL) ) {
 3422                     sidOK = PR_FALSE;
 3423                 }
 3424                 if (wrapKey) PK11_FreeSymKey(wrapKey);
 3425                 PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 3426                 slot = NULL;
 3427             }
 3428         }
 3429         /* If we previously did client-auth, make sure that the token that
 3430         ** holds the private key still exists, is logged in, hasn't been
 3431         ** removed, etc.
 3432         */
 3433         if (sidOK && !ssl3_ClientAuthTokenPresent(sid)) {
 3434             sidOK = PR_FALSE;
 3435         }
 3436 
 3437         if (!sidOK) {
 3438             SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].sch_sid_cache_not_ok );
 3439             (*ss->sec.uncache)(sid);
 3440             ssl_FreeSID(sid);
 3441             sid = NULL;
 3442         }
 3443     }
 3444 
 3445     if (sid) {
 3446         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].sch_sid_cache_hits );
 3447 
 3448         rv[1] = ssl3_NegotiateVersion(ss, sid->version[2][3]);
 3449         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess)
 3450             return rv[1];        /* error code was set */
 3451 
 3452         PRINT_BUF(4, (ss, "client, found session-id:", sid->u.ssl3.sessionID,
 3453                       sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength));
 3454 
 3455         ss->ssl3.policy = sid->u.ssl3.policy;
 3456     } else {
 3457         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].sch_sid_cache_misses );
 3458 
 3459         rv[1] = ssl3_NegotiateVersion(ss, SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_1_TLS);
 3460         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess)
 3461             return rv[1];        /* error code was set */
 3462 
 3463         sid = ssl3_NewSessionID(ss, PR_FALSE);
 3464         if (!sid) {
 3465             return SECFailure;        /* memory error is set */
 3466         }
 3467     }
 3468 
 3469     ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);
 3470     cwSpec = ss->ssl3.cwSpec;
 3471     if (cwSpec->mac_def->mac == mac_null) {
 3472         /* SSL records are not being MACed. */
 3473         cwSpec->version[2][3] = ss->version[2][3];
 3474     }
 3475     ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 3476 
 3477     if (ss->sec.ci.sid != NULL) {
 3478         ssl_FreeSID(ss->sec.ci.sid);        /* decrement ref count, free if zero */
 3479     }
 3480     ss->sec.ci.sid = sid;
 3481 
 3482     ss->sec.send = ssl3_SendApplicationData;
 3483 
 3484     /* shouldn't get here if SSL3 is disabled, but ... */
 3485     PORT_Assert[1](ss->opt.enableSSL3 || ss->opt.enableTLS);
 3486     if (!ss->opt.enableSSL3 && !ss->opt.enableTLS) {
 3487         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_SSL_DISABLED);
 3488             return SECFailure;
 3489     }
 3490 
 3491     /* how many suites does our PKCS11 support (regardless of policy)? */
 3492     num_suites = ssl3_config_match_init(ss);
 3493     if (!num_suites)
 3494             return SECFailure;        /* ssl3_config_match_init has set error code. */
 3495 
 3496     if (ss->opt.enableTLS) {
 3497         PRUint32 maxBytes = 65535; /* 2^16 - 1 */
 3498         PRInt32  extLen;
 3499 
 3500         extLen = ssl3_CallHelloExtensionSenders(ss, PR_FALSE, maxBytes, NULL);
 3501         if (extLen < 0) {
 3502             return SECFailure;
 3503         }
 3504         maxBytes        -= extLen;
 3505         total_exten_len += extLen;
 3506 
 3507         if (total_exten_len > 0)
 3508             total_exten_len += 2;
 3509     }
 3510 
 3511     /* how many suites are permitted by policy and user preference? */
 3512     num_suites = count_cipher_suites(ss, ss->ssl3.policy, PR_TRUE);
 3513     if (!num_suites)
 3514             return SECFailure;        /* count_cipher_suites has set error code. */
 3515 
 3516     length[1][2] = sizeof(SSL3ProtocolVersion) + SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH +
 3517         1 + ((sid == NULL) ? 0 : sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength) +
 3518         2 + num_suites*sizeof(ssl3CipherSuite) +
 3519         1 + compressionMethodsCount + total_exten_len;
 3520 
 3521     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, client_hello, length[1][2]);
 3522     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3523         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3524     }
 3525 
 3526     ss->clientHelloVersion = ss->version[2][3];
 3527     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, ss->clientHelloVersion, 2);
 3528     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3529         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3530     }
 3531     rv[1] = ssl3_GetNewRandom(&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random);
 3532     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3533         return rv[1];        /* err set by GetNewRandom. */
 3534     }
 3535     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(ss, &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random,
 3536                               SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH);
 3537     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3538         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3539     }
 3540 
 3541     if (sid)
 3542         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(
 3543             ss, sid->u.ssl3.sessionID, sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength, 1);
 3544     else
 3545         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, NULL, 0, 1);
 3546     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3547         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3548     }
 3549 
 3550     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, num_suites*sizeof(ssl3CipherSuite), 2);
 3551     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3552         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3553     }
 3554 
 3555 
 3556     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < i[2][3][4][10]mpl.h.dep.html#ssl_V3_SUITES_IMPLEMENTED">ssl_V3_SUITES_IMPLEMENTED; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 3557         ssl3Ci[2][3][4][10]pherSui[2][3][4][10]teCfg *sui[2][3][4][10]te = &ss->ci[2][3][4][10]pherSui[2][3][4][10]tes[i[2][3][4][10]];
 3558         if (config_match(suite, ss->ssl3.policy, PR_TRUE)) {
 3559             actual_count++;
 3560             if (actual_count > num_suites) {
 3561                 /* set error card removal/insertion error */
 3562                 PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_TOKEN_INSERTION_REMOVAL);
 3563                 return SECFailure;
 3564             }
 3565             rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, suite->cipher_suite,
 3566                                             sizeof(ssl3CipherSuite));
 3567             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3568                 return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3569             }
 3570         }
 3571     }
 3572 
 3573     /* if cards were removed or inserted between count_cipher_suites and
 3574      * generating our list, detect the error here rather than send it off to
 3575      * the server.. */
 3576     if (actual_count != num_suites) {
 3577         /* Card removal/insertion error */
 3578         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_TOKEN_INSERTION_REMOVAL);
 3579         return SECFailure;
 3580     }
 3581 
 3582     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, compressionMethodsCount, 1);
 3583     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3584         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3585     }
 3586     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < compressi[2][3][4][10]onMethodsCount; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 3587         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, compressi[2][3][4][10]ons[i[2][3][4][10]], 1);
 3588         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3589             return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 3590         }
 3591     }
 3592 
 3593     if (total_exten_len) {
 3594         PRUint32 maxBytes = total_exten_len - 2;
 3595         PRInt32  extLen;
 3596 
 3597         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, maxBytes, 2);
 3598         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3599             return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 3600         }
 3601 
 3602         extLen = ssl3_CallHelloExtensionSenders(ss, PR_TRUE, maxBytes, NULL);
 3603         if (extLen < 0) {
 3604             return SECFailure;
 3605         }
 3606         maxBytes -= extLen;
 3607         PORT_Assert[1](!maxBytes);
 3608     }
 3609 
 3610 
 3611     rv[1] = ssl3_FlushHandshake(ss, 0);
 3612     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 3613         return rv[1];        /* error code set by ssl3_FlushHandshake */
 3614     }
 3615 
 3616     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_server_hello;
 3617     return rv[1];
 3618 }
 3619 
 3620 
 3621 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 3622  * ssl3 Hello Request.
 3623  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 3624  */
 3625 static SECStatus
 3626 ssl3_HandleHelloRequest(sslSocket *ss)
 3627 {
 3628     sslSessionID *sid = ss->sec.ci.sid;
 3629     SECStatus     rv[1];
 3630 
 3631     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle hello_request handshake",
 3632                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 3633 
 3634     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 3635     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 3636 
 3637     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws == wait_server_hello)
 3638         return SECSuccess;
 3639     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != idle_handshake || ss->sec.isServer) {
 3640         (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 3641         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_HELLO_REQUEST);
 3642         return SECFailure;
 3643     }
 3644     if (sid) {
 3645         ss->sec.uncache(sid);
 3646         ssl_FreeSID(sid);
 3647         ss->sec.ci.sid = NULL;
 3648     }
 3649 
 3650     ssl_GetXmitBufLock(ss);
 3651     rv[1] = ssl3_SendClientHello(ss);
 3652     ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 3653 
 3654     return rv[1];
 3655 }
 3656 
 3657 #define UNKNOWN_WRAP_MECHANISM 0x7fffffff
 3658 
 3659 static const CK_MECHANISM_TYPE wrapMechanismList[SSL_NUM_WRAP_MECHS] = {
 3660     CKM_DES3_ECB,
 3661     CKM_CAST5_ECB,
 3662     CKM_DES_ECB,
 3663     CKM_KEY_WRAP_LYNKS,
 3664     CKM_IDEA_ECB,
 3665     CKM_CAST3_ECB,
 3666     CKM_CAST_ECB,
 3667     CKM_RC5_ECB,
 3668     CKM_RC2_ECB,
 3669     CKM_CDMF_ECB,
 3670     CKM_SKIPJACK_WRAP,
 3671     CKM_SKIPJACK_CBC64,
 3672     CKM_AES_ECB,
 3673     UNKNOWN_WRAP_MECHANISM
 3674 };
 3675 
 3676 static int
 3677 ssl_FindIndexByWrapMechanism(CK_MECHANISM_TYPE mech)
 3678 {
 3679     const CK_MECHANISM_TYPE *pMech = wrapMechanismList[1];
 3680 
 3681     while (mech != *pMech && *pMech != UNKNOWN_WRAP_MECHANISM) {
 3682             ++pMech;
 3683     }
 3684     return (*pMech == UNKNOWN_WRAP_MECHANISM) ? -1
 3685                                               : (pMech - wrapMechanismList[1]);
 3686 }
 3687 
 3688 static PK11SymKey *
 3689 ssl_UnwrapSymWrappingKey(
 3690         SSLWrappedSymWrappingKey *pWswk,
 3691         SECKEYPrivateKey *        svrPrivKey,
 3692         SSL3KEAType               exchKeyType,
 3693         CK_MECHANISM_TYPE         masterWrapMech,
 3694         void *                    pwArg)
 3695 {
 3696     PK11SymKey *             unwrappedWrappingKey  = NULL;
 3697     SECItem                  wrappedKey;
 3698 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 3699     PK11SymKey *             Ks;
 3700     SECKEYPublicKey          pubWrapKey;
 3701     ECCWrappedKeyInfo        *ecWrapped;
 3702 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 3703 
 3704     /* found the wrapping key on disk. */
 3705     PORT_Assert[1](pWswk->symWrapMechanism == masterWrapMech);
 3706     PORT_Assert[1](pWswk->exchKeyType      == exchKeyType);
 3707     if (pWswk->symWrapMechanism != masterWrapMech ||
 3708         pWswk->exchKeyType      != exchKeyType) {
 3709         goto loser;
 3710     }
 3711     wrappedKey.type = siBuffer;
 3712     wrappedKey.data[2] = pWswk->wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey;
 3713     wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = pWswk->wrappedSymKeyLen;
 3714     PORT_Assert[1](wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] <= sizeof pWswk->wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey);
 3715 
 3716     switch (exchKeyType) {
 3717 
 3718     case kt_rsa:
 3719         unwrappedWrappingKey =
 3720             PK11_PubUnwrapSymKey(svrPrivKey, &wrappedKey,
 3721                                  masterWrapMech, CKA_UNWRAP, 0);
 3722         break;
 3723 
 3724 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 3725     case kt_ecdh:
 3726         /* 
 3727          * For kt_ecdh, we first create an EC public key based on
 3728          * data stored with the wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey. Next,
 3729          * we do an ECDH computation involving this public key and
 3730          * the SSL server's (long-term) EC private key. The resulting
 3731          * shared secret is treated the same way as Fortezza's Ks, i.e.,
 3732          * it is used to recover the symmetric wrapping key.
 3733          *
 3734          * The data in wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey is laid out as defined
 3735          * in the ECCWrappedKeyInfo structure.
 3736          */
 3737         ecWrapped = (ECCWrappedKeyInfo *) pWswk->wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey;
 3738 
 3739         PORT_Assert[1](ecWrapped->encodedParamLen + ecWrapped->pubValueLen + 
 3740             ecWrapped->wrappedKeyLen <= MAX_EC_WRAPPED_KEY_BUFLEN);
 3741 
 3742         if (ecWrapped->encodedParamLen + ecWrapped->pubValueLen + 
 3743             ecWrapped->wrappedKeyLen > MAX_EC_WRAPPED_KEY_BUFLEN) {
 3744             PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 3745             goto loser;
 3746         }
 3747 
 3748         pubWrapKey.keyType = ecKey;
 3749         pubWrapKey.u.ec.size[4][8][9] = ecWrapped->size[4][8][9];
 3750         pubWrapKey.u.ec.DEREncodedParams.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = ecWrapped->encodedParamLen;
 3751         pubWrapKey.u.ec.DEREncodedParams.data[2] = ecWrapped->var;
 3752         pubWrapKey.u.ec.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = ecWrapped->pubValueLen;
 3753         pubWrapKey.u.ec.publicValue.data[2] = ecWrapped->var + 
 3754             ecWrapped->encodedParamLen;
 3755 
 3756         wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = ecWrapped->wrappedKeyLen;
 3757         wrappedKey.data[2] = ecWrapped->var + ecWrapped->encodedParamLen + 
 3758             ecWrapped->pubValueLen;
 3759         
 3760         /* Derive Ks using ECDH */
 3761         Ks = PK11_PubDeriveWithKDF(svrPrivKey, &pubWrapKey, PR_FALSE, NULL,
 3762                                    NULL, CKM_ECDH1_DERIVE, masterWrapMech, 
 3763                                    CKA_DERIVE, 0, NULL">CKD_NULL, NULL, NULL);
 3764         if (Ks == NULL) {
 3765             goto loser;
 3766         }
 3767 
 3768         /*  Use Ks to unwrap the wrapping key */
 3769         unwrappedWrappingKey = PK11_UnwrapSymKey(Ks, masterWrapMech, NULL, 
 3770                                                  &wrappedKey, masterWrapMech, 
 3771                                                  CKA_UNWRAP, 0);
 3772         PK11_FreeSymKey(Ks);
 3773         
 3774         break;
 3775 #endif
 3776 
 3777     default:
 3778         /* Assert? */
 3779         SET_ERROR_CODE[1][2][3][4][5]
 3780         goto loser;
 3781     }
 3782 loser:
 3783     return unwrappedWrappingKey;
 3784 }
 3785 
 3786 /* Each process sharing the server session ID cache has its own array of
 3787  * SymKey pointers for the symmetric wrapping keys that are used to wrap
 3788  * the master secrets.  There is one key for each KEA type.  These Symkeys
 3789  * correspond to the wrapped SymKeys kept in the server session cache.
 3790  */
 3791 
 3792 typedef struct {
 3793     PK11SymKey *      symWrapKey[kt_kea_size];
 3794 } ssl3SymWrapKey;
 3795 
 3796 static PZLock *          symWrapKeysLock = NULL;
 3797 static ssl3SymWrapKey    symWrapKeys[SSL_NUM_WRAP_MECHS];
 3798 
 3799 SECStatus
 3800 SSL3_ShutdownServerCache(void)
 3801 {
 3802     i[2][3][4][10]nt             i[2][3][4][10], j;
 3803 
 3804     if (!symWrapKeysLock)
 3805             return SECSuccess;        /* was never initialized */
 3806     PZ_Lock(symWrapKeysLock);
 3807     /* get rid of all symWrapKeys */
 3808     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < SSL_NUM_WRAP_MECHS; ++i[2][3][4][10]) {
 3809             for (j = 0; j < kt_kea_size; ++j) {
 3810             PK11SymKey **   pSymWrapKey;
 3811             pSymWrapKey = &symWrapKeys[i[2][3][4][10]].symWrapKey[j];
 3812             if (*pSymWrapKey) {
 3813                 PK11_FreeSymKey(*pSymWrapKey);
 3814                     *pSymWrapKey = NULL;
 3815             }
 3816         }
 3817     }
 3818 
 3819     PZ_Unlock(symWrapKeysLock);
 3820     return SECSuccess;
 3821 }
 3822 
 3823 void ssl_InitSymWrapKeysLock(void)
 3824 {
 3825     /* atomically initialize the lock */
 3826     if (!symWrapKeysLock)
 3827         nss_InitLock[1](&symWrapKeysLock, nssILockOther);
 3828 }
 3829 
 3830 /* Try to get wrapping key for mechanism from in-memory array.
 3831  * If that fails, look for one on disk.
 3832  * If that fails, generate a new one, put the new one on disk,
 3833  * Put the new key in the in-memory array.
 3834  */
 3835 static PK11SymKey *
 3836 getWrappingKey( sslSocket *       ss,
 3837                 PK11SlotInfo *    masterSecretSlot,
 3838                 SSL3KEAType       exchKeyType,
 3839                 CK_MECHANISM_TYPE masterWrapMech,
 3840                 void *            pwArg)
 3841 {
 3842     SECKEYPrivateKey *       svrPrivKey;
 3843     SECKEYPublicKey *        svrPubKey             = NULL;
 3844     PK11SymKey *             unwrappedWrappingKey  = NULL;
 3845     PK11SymKey **            pSymWrapKey;
 3846     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE        asymWrapMechanism = CKM_INVALID_MECHANISM;
 3847     int                      length[1][2];
 3848     int                      symWrapMechIndex;
 3849     SECStatus                rv[1];
 3850     SECItem                  wrappedKey;
 3851     SSLWrappedSymWrappingKey wswk;
 3852 
 3853     svrPrivKey  = ss->serverCerts[exchKeyType].SERVERKEY;
 3854     PORT_Assert[1](svrPrivKey != NULL);
 3855     if (!svrPrivKey) {
 3856             return NULL;        /* why are we here?!? */
 3857     }
 3858 
 3859     symWrapMechIndex = ssl_FindIndexByWrapMechanism(masterWrapMech);
 3860     PORT_Assert[1](symWrapMechIndex >= 0);
 3861     if (symWrapMechIndex < 0)
 3862             return NULL;        /* invalid masterWrapMech. */
 3863 
 3864     pSymWrapKey = &symWrapKeys[symWrapMechIndex].symWrapKey[exchKeyType];
 3865 
 3866     ssl_InitSymWrapKeysLock();
 3867 
 3868     PZ_Lock(symWrapKeysLock);
 3869 
 3870     unwrappedWrappingKey = *pSymWrapKey;
 3871     if (unwrappedWrappingKey != NULL) {
 3872         if (PK11_VerifyKeyOK(unwrappedWrappingKey)) {
 3873             unwrappedWrappingKey = PK11_ReferenceSymKey(unwrappedWrappingKey);
 3874             goto done;
 3875         }
 3876         /* slot series has changed, so this key is no good any more. */
 3877         PK11_FreeSymKey(unwrappedWrappingKey);
 3878         *pSymWrapKey = unwrappedWrappingKey = NULL;
 3879     }
 3880 
 3881     /* Try to get wrapped SymWrapping key out of the (disk) cache. */
 3882     /* Following call fills in wswk on success. */
 3883     if (ssl_GetWrappingKey(symWrapMechIndex, exchKeyType, &wswk)) {
 3884             /* found the wrapped sym wrapping key on disk. */
 3885         unwrappedWrappingKey =
 3886             ssl_UnwrapSymWrappingKey(&wswk, svrPrivKey, exchKeyType,
 3887                                      masterWrapMech, pwArg);
 3888         if (unwrappedWrappingKey) {
 3889             goto install;
 3890         }
 3891     }
 3892 
 3893     if (!masterSecretSlot)         /* caller doesn't want to create a new one. */
 3894             goto loser;
 3895 
 3896     length[1][2] = PK11_GetBestKeyLength(masterSecretSlot, masterWrapMech);
 3897     /* Zero length means fixed key length algorithm, or error.
 3898      * It's ambiguous.
 3899      */
 3900     unwrappedWrappingKey = PK11_KeyGen(masterSecretSlot, masterWrapMech, NULL,
 3901                                        length[1][2], pwArg);
 3902     if (!unwrappedWrappingKey) {
 3903             goto loser;
 3904     }
 3905 
 3906     /* Prepare the buffer to receive the wrappedWrappingKey,
 3907      * the symmetric wrapping key wrapped using the server's pub key.
 3908      */
 3909     PORT_Memset(&wswk, 0, sizeof wswk);        /* eliminate UMRs. */
 3910 
 3911     if (ss->serverCerts[exchKeyType].serverKeyPair) {
 3912         svrPubKey = ss->serverCerts[exchKeyType].serverKeyPair->pubKey;
 3913     }
 3914     if (svrPubKey == NULL) {
 3915         PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 3916         goto loser;
 3917     }
 3918     wrappedKey.type = siBuffer;
 3919     wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = SECKEY_PublicKeyStrength(svrPubKey);
 3920     wrappedKey.data[2] = wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey;
 3921 
 3922     PORT_Assert[1](wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] <= sizeof wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey);
 3923     if (wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > sizeof wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey)
 3924             goto loser;
 3925 
 3926     /* wrap symmetric wrapping key in server's public key. */
 3927     switch (exchKeyType) {
 3928 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 3929     PK11SymKey *      Ks;
 3930     SECKEYPublicKey   *pubWrapKey = NULL;
 3931     SECKEYPrivateKey  *privWrapKey = NULL;
 3932     ECCWrappedKeyInfo *ecWrapped;
 3933 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 3934 
 3935     case kt_rsa:
 3936         asymWrapMechanism = CKM_RSA_PKCS;
 3937         rv[1] = PK11_PubWrapSymKey(asymWrapMechanism, svrPubKey,
 3938                                 unwrappedWrappingKey, &wrappedKey);
 3939         break;
 3940 
 3941 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 3942     case kt_ecdh:
 3943         /*
 3944          * We generate an ephemeral EC key pair. Perform an ECDH
 3945          * computation involving this ephemeral EC public key and
 3946          * the SSL server's (long-term) EC private key. The resulting
 3947          * shared secret is treated in the same way as Fortezza's Ks, 
 3948          * i.e., it is used to wrap the wrapping key. To facilitate
 3949          * unwrapping in ssl_UnwrapWrappingKey, we also store all
 3950          * relevant info about the ephemeral EC public key in
 3951          * wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey and lay it out as 
 3952          * described in the ECCWrappedKeyInfo structure.
 3953          */
 3954         PORT_Assert[1](svrPubKey->keyType == ecKey);
 3955         if (svrPubKey->keyType != ecKey) {
 3956             /* something is wrong in sslsecur.c if this isn't an ecKey */
 3957             PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 3958             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 3959             goto ec_cleanup;
 3960         }
 3961 
 3962         privWrapKey = SECKEY_CreateECPrivateKey(
 3963             &svrPubKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams, &pubWrapKey, NULL);
 3964         if ((privWrapKey == NULL) || (pubWrapKey == NULL)) {
 3965             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 3966             goto ec_cleanup;
 3967         }
 3968         
 3969         /* Set the key size in bits */
 3970         if (pubWrapKey->u.ec.size[4][8][9] == 0) {
 3971             pubWrapKey->u.ec.size[4][8][9] = SECKEY_PublicKeyStrengthInBits(svrPubKey);
 3972         }
 3973 
 3974         PORT_Assert[1](pubWrapKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 
 3975             pubWrapKey->u.ec.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] < MAX_EC_WRAPPED_KEY_BUFLEN);
 3976         if (pubWrapKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 
 3977             pubWrapKey->u.ec.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] >= MAX_EC_WRAPPED_KEY_BUFLEN) {
 3978             PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_INVALID_KEY);
 3979             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 3980             goto ec_cleanup;
 3981         }
 3982 
 3983         /* Derive Ks using ECDH */
 3984         Ks = PK11_PubDeriveWithKDF(svrPrivKey, pubWrapKey, PR_FALSE, NULL,
 3985                                    NULL, CKM_ECDH1_DERIVE, masterWrapMech, 
 3986                                    CKA_DERIVE, 0, NULL">CKD_NULL, NULL, NULL);
 3987         if (Ks == NULL) {
 3988             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 3989             goto ec_cleanup;
 3990         }
 3991 
 3992         ecWrapped = (ECCWrappedKeyInfo *) (wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey);
 3993         ecWrapped->size[4][8][9] = pubWrapKey->u.ec.size[4][8][9];
 3994         ecWrapped->encodedParamLen = pubWrapKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 3995         PORT_Memcpy(ecWrapped->var, pubWrapKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams.data[2], 
 3996             pubWrapKey->u.ec.DEREncodedParams.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 3997 
 3998         ecWrapped->pubValueLen = pubWrapKey->u.ec.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 3999         PORT_Memcpy(ecWrapped->var + ecWrapped->encodedParamLen, 
 4000                     pubWrapKey->u.ec.publicValue.data[2], 
 4001                     pubWrapKey->u.ec.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4002 
 4003         wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = MAX_EC_WRAPPED_KEY_BUFLEN - 
 4004             (ecWrapped->encodedParamLen + ecWrapped->pubValueLen);
 4005         wrappedKey.data[2] = ecWrapped->var + ecWrapped->encodedParamLen +
 4006             ecWrapped->pubValueLen;
 4007 
 4008         /* wrap symmetricWrapping key with the local Ks */
 4009         rv[1] = PK11_WrapSymKey(masterWrapMech, NULL, Ks,
 4010                              unwrappedWrappingKey, &wrappedKey);
 4011 
 4012         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4013             goto ec_cleanup;
 4014         }
 4015 
 4016         /* Write down the length of wrapped key in the buffer
 4017          * wswk.wrappedSymmetricWrappingkey at the appropriate offset
 4018          */
 4019         ecWrapped->wrappedKeyLen = wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4020 
 4021 ec_cleanup:
 4022         if (privWrapKey) SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(privWrapKey);
 4023         if (pubWrapKey) SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(pubWrapKey);
 4024         if (Ks) PK11_FreeSymKey(Ks);
 4025         asymWrapMechanism = masterWrapMech;
 4026         break;
 4027 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 4028 
 4029     default:
 4030         rv[1] = SECFailure;
 4031         break;
 4032     }
 4033 
 4034     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4035         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4036         goto loser;
 4037     }
 4038 
 4039     PORT_Assert[1](asymWrapMechanism != CKM_INVALID_MECHANISM);
 4040 
 4041     wswk.symWrapMechanism  = masterWrapMech;
 4042     wswk.symWrapMechIndex  = symWrapMechIndex;
 4043     wswk.asymWrapMechanism = asymWrapMechanism;
 4044     wswk.exchKeyType       = exchKeyType;
 4045     wswk.wrappedSymKeyLen  = wrappedKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4046 
 4047     /* put it on disk. */
 4048     /* If the wrapping key for this KEA type has already been set, 
 4049      * then abandon the value we just computed and 
 4050      * use the one we got from the disk.
 4051      */
 4052     if (ssl_SetWrappingKey(&wswk)) {
 4053             /* somebody beat us to it.  The original contents of our wswk
 4054          * has been replaced with the content on disk.  Now, discard
 4055          * the key we just created and unwrap this new one.
 4056          */
 4057             PK11_FreeSymKey(unwrappedWrappingKey);
 4058 
 4059         unwrappedWrappingKey =
 4060             ssl_UnwrapSymWrappingKey(&wswk, svrPrivKey, exchKeyType,
 4061                                      masterWrapMech, pwArg);
 4062     }
 4063 
 4064 install:
 4065     if (unwrappedWrappingKey) {
 4066         *pSymWrapKey = PK11_ReferenceSymKey(unwrappedWrappingKey);
 4067     }
 4068 
 4069 loser:
 4070 done:
 4071     PZ_Unlock(symWrapKeysLock);
 4072     return unwrappedWrappingKey;
 4073 }

 4076 /* Called from ssl3_SendClientKeyExchange(). */
 4077 /* Presently, this always uses PKCS11.  There is no bypass for this. */
 4078 static SECStatus
 4079 sendRSAClientKeyExchange(sslSocket * ss, SECKEYPublicKey * svrPubKey)
 4080 {
 4081     PK11SymKey *        pms                 = NULL;
 4082     SECStatus           rv[1]                    = SECFailure;
 4083     SECItem                 enc_pms         = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4084     PRBool              isTLS;
 4085 
 4086     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 4087     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 4088 
 4089     /* Generate the pre-master secret ...  */
 4090     ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);
 4091     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 4092 
 4093     pms = ssl3_GenerateRSAPMS(ss, ss->ssl3.pwSpec, NULL);
 4094     ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 4095     if (pms == NULL) {
 4096         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4097         goto loser;
 4098     }
 4099 
 4100     /* Get the wrapped (encrypted) pre-master secret, enc_pms */
 4101     enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = SECKEY_PublicKeyStrength(svrPubKey);
 4102     enc_pms.data[2] = (unsigned char*)PORT_Alloc(enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4103     if (enc_pms.data[2] == NULL) {
 4104         goto loser;        /* err set by PORT_Alloc */
 4105     }
 4106 
 4107     /* wrap pre-master secret in server's public key. */
 4108     rv[1] = PK11_PubWrapSymKey(CKM_RSA_PKCS, svrPubKey, pms, &enc_pms);
 4109     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4110         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4111         goto loser;
 4112     }
 4113 
 4114     rv[1] = ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(ss,  pms);
 4115     PK11_FreeSymKey(pms); pms = NULL;
 4116 
 4117     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4118         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4119         goto loser;
 4120     }
 4121 
 4122     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, client_key_exchange, 
 4123                                     isTLS ? enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 2 : enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4124     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4125         goto loser;        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 4126     }
 4127     if (isTLS) {
 4128             rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, enc_pms.data[2], enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);
 4129     } else {
 4130         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(ss, enc_pms.data[2], enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4131     }
 4132     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4133         goto loser;        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 4134     }
 4135 
 4136     rv[1] = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 4137 
 4138 loser:
 4139     if (enc_pms.data[2] != NULL) {
 4140         PORT_Free(enc_pms.data[2]);
 4141     }
 4142     if (pms != NULL) {
 4143             PK11_FreeSymKey(pms);
 4144     }
 4145     return rv[1];
 4146 }

 4148 /* Called from ssl3_SendClientKeyExchange(). */
 4149 /* Presently, this always uses PKCS11.  There is no bypass for this. */
 4150 static SECStatus
 4151 sendDHClientKeyExchange(sslSocket * ss, SECKEYPublicKey * svrPubKey)
 4152 {
 4153     PK11SymKey *        pms                 = NULL;
 4154     SECStatus           rv[1]                    = SECFailure;
 4155     PRBool              isTLS;
 4156     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE        target;
 4157 
 4158     SECKEYDHParams        dhParam;                /* DH parameters */
 4159     SECKEYPublicKey        *pubKey = NULL;                /* Ephemeral DH key */
 4160     SECKEYPrivateKey        *privKey = NULL;        /* Ephemeral DH key */
 4161 
 4162     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 4163     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 4164 
 4165     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 4166 
 4167     /* Copy DH parameters from server key */
 4168 
 4169     dhParam.prime.data[2] = svrPubKey->u.dh.prime.data[2];
 4170     dhParam.prime.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = svrPubKey->u.dh.prime.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4171     dhParam.base[1][2][3][4][5][6].data[2] = svrPubKey->u.dh.base[1][2][3][4][5][6].data[2];
 4172     dhParam.base[1][2][3][4][5][6].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = svrPubKey->u.dh.base[1][2][3][4][5][6].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4173 
 4174     /* Generate ephemeral DH keypair */
 4175     privKey = SECKEY_CreateDHPrivateKey(&dhParam, &pubKey, NULL);
 4176     if (!privKey || !pubKey) {
 4177             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SEC_ERROR_KEYGEN_FAIL);
 4178             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 4179             goto loser;
 4180     }
 4181     PRINT_BUF(50, (ss, "DH public value[1][2]:",
 4182                                         pubKey->u.dh.publicValue.data[2],
 4183                                         pubKey->u.dh.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 4184 
 4185     if (isTLS) target = CKM_TLS_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_DH;
 4186     else target = CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE_DH;
 4187 
 4188     /* Determine the PMS */
 4189 
 4190     pms = PK11_PubDerive(privKey, svrPubKey, PR_FALSE, NULL, NULL,
 4191                             CKM_DH_PKCS_DERIVE, target, CKA_DERIVE, 0, NULL);
 4192 
 4193     if (pms == NULL) {
 4194         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4195         goto loser;
 4196     }
 4197 
 4198     SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(privKey);
 4199     privKey = NULL;
 4200 
 4201     rv[1] = ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(ss,  pms);
 4202     PK11_FreeSymKey(pms); pms = NULL;
 4203 
 4204     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4205         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4206         goto loser;
 4207     }
 4208 
 4209     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, client_key_exchange, 
 4210                                         pubKey->u.dh.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 2);
 4211     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4212         goto loser;        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 4213     }
 4214     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, 
 4215                                         pubKey->u.dh.publicValue.data[2],
 4216                                         pubKey->u.dh.publicValue.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);
 4217     SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(pubKey);
 4218     pubKey = NULL;
 4219 
 4220     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4221         goto loser;        /* err set by ssl3_AppendHandshake* */
 4222     }
 4223 
 4224     rv[1] = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 4225 
 4226 
 4227 loser:
 4228 
 4229     if(pms) PK11_FreeSymKey(pms);
 4230     if(privKey) SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(privKey);
 4231     if(pubKey) SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(pubKey);
 4232     return rv[1];
 4233 }

 4239 /* Called from ssl3_HandleServerHelloDone(). */
 4240 static SECStatus
 4241 ssl3_SendClientKeyExchange(sslSocket *ss)
 4242 {
 4243     SECKEYPublicKey *        serverKey         = NULL;
 4244     SECStatus                 rv[1]                 = SECFailure;
 4245     PRBool              isTLS;
 4246 
 4247     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send client_key_exchange handshake",
 4248                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 4249 
 4250     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 4251     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 4252 
 4253     if (ss->sec.peerKey == NULL) {
 4254         serverKey = CERT_ExtractPublicKey(ss->sec.peerCert);
 4255         if (serverKey == NULL) {
 4256             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_EXTRACT_PUBLIC_KEY_FAILURE);
 4257             return SECFailure;
 4258         }
 4259     } else {
 4260         serverKey = ss->sec.peerKey;
 4261         ss->sec.peerKey = NULL; /* we're done with it now */
 4262     }
 4263 
 4264     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 4265     /* enforce limits on kea key sizes. */
 4266     if (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->is_limited) {
 4267         int keyLen = SECKEY_PublicKeyStrength(serverKey);        /* bytes */
 4268 
 4269         if (keyLen * BPB[1][2] > ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->key_size_limit) {
 4270             if (isTLS)
 4271                 (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, export_restriction);
 4272             else
 4273                 (void)ssl3_HandshakeFailure(ss);
 4274             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_PUB_KEY_SIZE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED);
 4275             goto loser;
 4276         }
 4277     }
 4278 
 4279     ss->sec.keaType    = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType;
 4280     ss->sec.keaKeyBits = seckey.c.dep.html#SECKEY_PublicKeyStrengthInBits">SECKEY_PublicKeyStrengthInBits(serverKey);
 4281 
 4282     switch (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType) {
 4283     case kt_rsa:
 4284         rv[1] = sendRSAClientKeyExchange(ss, serv[1]erKey);
 4285         break;
 4286 
 4287     case kt_dh:
 4288         rv[1] = sendDHClientKeyExchange(ss, serv[1]erKey);
 4289         break;
 4290 
 4291 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 4292     case kt_ecdh:
 4293         rv[1] = ssl3_SendECDHClientKeyExchange(ss, serv[1]erKey);
 4294         break;
 4295 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 4296 
 4297     default:
 4298         /* got an unknown or unsupported Key Exchange Algorithm.  */
 4299         SEND_ALERT
 4300         PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_KEYALG);
 4301         break;
 4302     }
 4303 
 4304     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: DONE sending client_key_exchange",
 4305                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 4306 
 4307 loser:
 4308     if (serverKey) 
 4309             SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(serverKey);
 4310     return rv[1];        /* err code already set. */
 4311 }

 4371     }

 4379 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 4380  * ssl3 ServerHello message.
 4381  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.

 4383 static SECStatus
 4384 ssl3_HandleServerHello(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2])

 4401     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
