 4416             goto loser;         /* alert has been sent */
 4417     }
 4418     version[2][3] = (SSL3ProtocolVersion)temp;
 4419 
 4420     /* this is appropriate since the negotiation is complete, and we only
 4421     ** know SSL 3.x.
 4422     */
 4423     if (MSB(version[2][3]) != MSB(SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0)) {
 4424             desc = (version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0) ? protocol_version[2][3] 
 4425                                                    : handshake_failure;
 4426         goto alert_loser;
 4427     }
 4428 
 4429     rv[1] = ssl3_NegotiateVersion(ss, version[2][3]);
 4430     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4431             desc = (version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0) ? protocol_version[2][3] 
 4432                                                    : handshake_failure;
 4433         errCode = SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP;
 4434         goto alert_loser;
 4435     }
 4436     isTLS = (ss->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 4437 
 4438     rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshake(
 4439         ss, &ss->ssl3.hs.server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4440     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4441             goto loser;         /* alert has been sent */
 4442     }
 4443 
 4444     rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &sidBytes, 1, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4445     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4446             goto loser;         /* alert has been sent */
 4447     }
 4448     if (sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > SSL3_SESSIONID_BYTES) {
 4449         if (isTLS)
 4450             desc = decode_error;
 4451         goto alert_loser;        /* malformed. */
 4452     }
 4453 
 4454     /* find selected cipher suite in our list. */
 4455     temp = b[2][5][8]er">ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumb[2][5][8]er(ss, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4456     if (temp < 0) {
 4457             goto loser;         /* alert has been sent */
 4458     }
 4459     ssl3_config_match_init(ss);
 4460     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < i[2][3][4][10]mpl.h.dep.html#ssl_V3_SUITES_IMPLEMENTED">ssl_V3_SUITES_IMPLEMENTED; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 4461         ssl3Ci[2][3][4][10]pherSui[2][3][4][10]teCfg *sui[2][3][4][10]te = &ss->ci[2][3][4][10]pherSui[2][3][4][10]tes[i[2][3][4][10]];
 4462         if ((temp == suite->cipher_suite) &&
 4463             (config_match(suite, ss->ssl3.policy, PR_TRUE))) {
 4464             suite_found = PR_TRUE;
 4465             break;        /* success */
 4466         }
 4467     }
 4468     if (!suite_found) {
 4469             desc    = handshake_failure;
 4470         errCode = SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP;
 4471         goto alert_loser;
 4472     }
 4473     ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite = (ssl3CipherSuite)temp;
 4474     ss->ssl3.hs.suite_def    = ssl_LookupCipherSuiteDef((ssl3CipherSuite)temp);
 4475     PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.hs.suite_def);
 4476     if (!ss->ssl3.hs.suite_def) {
 4477             PORT_SetError(errCode = SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 4478         goto loser;        /* we don't send alerts for our screw-ups. */
 4479     }
 4480 
 4481     /* find selected compression method in our list. */
 4482     temp = b[2][5][8]er">ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumb[2][5][8]er(ss, 1, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4483     if (temp < 0) {
 4484             goto loser;         /* alert has been sent */
 4485     }
 4486     suite_found = PR_FALSE;
 4487     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < compressi[2][3][4][10]onMethodsCount; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 4488         i[2][3][4][10]f (temp == compressi[2][3][4][10]ons[i[2][3][4][10]])  {
 4489             suite_found = PR_TRUE;
 4490             break;        /* success */
 4491             }
 4492     }
 4493     if (!suite_found) {
 4494             desc    = handshake_failure;
 4495         errCode = SSL_ERROR_NO_COMPRESSION_OVERLAP;
 4496         goto alert_loser;
 4497     }
 4498     ss->ssl3.hs.compression = (SSL3CompressionMethod)temp;
 4499 
 4500 #ifdef DISALLOW_SERVER_HELLO_EXTENSIONS
 4501     if (length[1][2] != 0) {        /* malformed */
 4502         goto alert_loser;
 4503     }
 4504 #endif
 4505 
 4506     /* Any errors after this point are not "malformed" errors. */
 4507     desc    = handshake_failure;
 4508 
 4509     /* we need to call ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec here so we can check the
 4510      * key exchange algorithm. */
 4511     rv[1] = ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec(ss);
 4512     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4513         goto alert_loser;        /* error code is set. */
 4514     }
 4515 
 4516     /* We may or may not have sent a session id, we may get one back or
 4517      * not and if so it may match the one we sent.
 4518      * Attempt to restore the master secret to see if this is so...
 4519      * Don't consider failure to find a matching SID an error.
 4520      */
 4521     sid_match = (PRBool)(sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > 0 &&
 4522         sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength &&
 4523         !PORT_Memcmp(sid->u.ssl3.sessionID, sidBytes.data[2], sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 4524 
 4525     if (sid_match &&
 4526         sid->version[2][3] == ss->version[2][3] &&
 4527         sid->u.ssl3.cipherSuite == ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite) do {
 4528         ssl3CipherSpec *pwSpec = ss->ssl3.pwSpec;
 4529 
 4530         SECItem       wrappedMS;   /* wrapped master secret. */
 4531 
 4532         ss->sec.authAlgorithm = sid->authAlgorithm;
 4533         ss->sec.authKeyBits   = sid->authKeyBits;
 4534         ss->sec.keaType       = sid->keaType;
 4535         ss->sec.keaKeyBits    = sid->keaKeyBits;
 4536 
 4537         /* 3 cases here:
 4538          * a) key is wrapped (implies using PKCS11)
 4539          * b) key is unwrapped, but we're still using PKCS11
 4540          * c) key is unwrapped, and we're bypassing PKCS11.
 4541          */
 4542         if (sid->u.ssl3.keys.msIsWrapped) {
 4543             PK11SlotInfo *slot;
 4544             PK11SymKey *  wrapKey;     /* wrapping key */
 4545             CK_FLAGS      keyFlags      = 0;
 4546 
 4547             if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 4548                 /* we cannot restart a non-bypass session in a 
 4549                 ** bypass socket.
 4550                 */
 4551                 break;  
 4552             }
 4553             /* unwrap master secret with PKCS11 */
 4554             slot = SECMOD_LookupSlot(sid->u.ssl3.masterModuleID,
 4555                                      sid->u.ssl3.masterSlotID);
 4556             if (slot == NULL) {
 4557                 break;                /* not considered an error. */
 4558             }
 4559             if (!slot.c.dep.html#PK11_IsPresent">PK11_IsPresent(slot)) {
 4560                 PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 4561                 break;                /* not considered an error. */
 4562             }
 4563             wrapKey = PK11_GetWrapKey(slot, sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapIndex,
 4564                                       sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapMech,
 4565                                       sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapSeries,
 4566                                       ss->pkcs11PinArg);
 4567             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 4568             if (wrapKey == NULL) {
 4569                 break;                /* not considered an error. */
 4570             }
 4571 
 4572             if (ss->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0) {        /* isTLS */
 4573                 keyFlags = CKF_SIGN | CKF_VERIFY;
 4574             }
 4575 
 4576             wrappedMS.data[2] = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 4577             wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4578             pwSpec->master_secret =
 4579                 PK11_UnwrapSymKeyWithFlags(wrapKey, sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapMech, 
 4580                             NULL, &wrappedMS, CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE,
 4581                             CKA_DERIVE, sizeof(SSL3MasterSecret), keyFlags);
 4582             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 4583             PK11_FreeSymKey(wrapKey);
 4584             if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 4585                 break;        /* errorCode set just after call to UnwrapSymKey. */
 4586             }
 4587         } else if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 4588             /* MS is not wrapped */
 4589             wrappedMS.data[2] = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 4590             wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4591             memcpy(pwSpec->raw_master_secret, wrappedMS.data[2], wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4592             pwSpec->msItem.data[2] = pwSpec->raw_master_secret;
 4593             pwSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4594         } else {
 4595             /* We CAN restart a bypass session in a non-bypass socket. */
 4596             /* need to import the raw master secret to session object */
 4597             PK11SlotInfo *slot = slot.c.dep.html#PK11_GetInternalSlot">PK11_GetInternalSlot();
 4598             wrappedMS.data[2] = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 4599             wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4600             pwSpec->master_secret =  
 4601                 PK11_ImportSymKey(slot, CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE, 
 4602                                   PK11_OriginUnwrap, CKA_ENCRYPT, 
 4603                                   &wrappedMS, NULL);
 4604             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 4605             if (pwSpec->master_secret == NULL) {
 4606                 break; 
 4607             }
 4608         }
 4609 
 4610         /* Got a Match */
 4611         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].hsh_sid_cache_hits );
 4612         ss->ssl3.hs.ws         = wait_change_cipher;
 4613         ss->ssl3.hs.isResuming = PR_TRUE;
 4614 
 4615         /* copy the peer cert from the SID */
 4616         if (sid->peerCert != NULL) {
 4617             ss->sec.peerCert = CERT_DupCertificate(sid->peerCert);
 4618         }
 4619 
 4620 
 4621         /* NULL value for PMS signifies re-use of the old MS */
 4622         rv[1] = ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(ss,  NULL);
 4623         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4624             goto alert_loser;        /* err code was set */
 4625         }
 4626         return SECSuccess;
 4627     } while (0);
 4628 
 4629     if (sid_match)
 4630         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].hsh_sid_cache_not_ok );
 4631     else
 4632         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].hsh_sid_cache_misses );
 4633 
 4634     /* throw the old one away */
 4635     sid->u.ssl3.keys.resumable = PR_FALSE;
 4636     (*ss->sec.uncache)(sid);
 4637     ssl_FreeSID(sid);
 4638 
 4639     /* get a new sid */
 4640     ss->sec.ci.sid = sid = ssl3_NewSessionID(ss, PR_FALSE);
 4641     if (sid == NULL) {
 4642         goto alert_loser;        /* memory error is set. */
 4643     }
 4644 
 4645     sid->version[2][3] = ss->version[2][3];
 4646     sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength = sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 4647     PORT_Memcpy(sid->u.ssl3.sessionID, sidBytes.data[2], sidBytes.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 4648 
 4649     ss->ssl3.hs.isResuming = PR_FALSE;
 4650     ss->ssl3.hs.ws         = wait_server_cert;
 4651     return SECSuccess;
 4652 
 4653 alert_loser:
 4654     (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 4655 
 4656 loser:
 4657     errCode = ssl_MapLowLevelError(errCode);
 4658     return SECFailure;
 4659 }
 4660 
 4661 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 4662  * ssl3 ServerKeyExchange message.
 4663  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 4664  */
 4665 static SECStatus
 4666 ssl3_HandleServerKeyExchange(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2])
 4667 {
 4668     PRArenaPool *    arena     = NULL;
 4669     SECKEYPublicKey *peerKey   = NULL;
 4670     PRBool           isTLS;
 4671     SECStatus        rv[1];
 4672     int              errCode   = SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_SERVER_KEY_EXCH;
 4673     SSL3AlertDescription desc  = illegal_parameter;
 4674     SSL3Hashes       hashes;
 4675     SECItem          signature = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4676 
 4677     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle server_key_exchange handshake",
 4678                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 4679     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 4680     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 4681 
 4682     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_server_key &&
 4683         ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_server_cert) {
 4684         errCode = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_SERVER_KEY_EXCH;
 4685         desc    = unexpected_message;
 4686         goto alert_loser;
 4687     }
 4688     if (ss->sec.peerCert == NULL) {
 4689         errCode = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_SERVER_KEY_EXCH;
 4690         desc    = unexpected_message;
 4691         goto alert_loser;
 4692     }
 4693 
 4694     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.prSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 4695 
 4696     switch (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType) {
 4697 
 4698     case kt_rsa: {
 4699         SECItem          modulus   = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4700         SECItem          exponent  = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4701 
 4702             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &modulus, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4703             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4704             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4705         }
 4706             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &exponent, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4707             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4708             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4709         }
 4710             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &signature, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4711             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4712             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4713         }
 4714             if (length[1][2] != 0) {
 4715             if (isTLS)
 4716                 desc = decode_error;
 4717             goto alert_loser;                /* malformed. */
 4718         }
 4719 
 4720         /* failures after this point are not malformed handshakes. */
 4721         /* TLS: send decrypt_error if signature failed. */
 4722             desc = isTLS ? decrypt_error : handshake_failure;
 4723 
 4724             /*
 4725               *  check to make sure the hash is signed by right guy
 4726               */
 4727             rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeExportRSAKeyHash(modulus, exponent,
 4728                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random,
 4729                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.server_random, 
 4730                                           &hashes, ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]);
 4731         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4732             errCode =
 4733                     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4734             goto alert_loser;
 4735         }
 4736         rv[1] = ssl3_VerifySignedHashes(&hashes, ss->sec.peerCert, &signature,
 4737                                     isTLS, ss->pkcs11PinArg);
 4738         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess)  {
 4739             errCode =
 4740                     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4741             goto alert_loser;
 4742         }
 4743 
 4744         /*
 4745          * we really need to build a new key here because we can no longer
 4746          * ignore calling SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey. Using the key may allocate
 4747          * pkcs11 slots and ID's.
 4748          */
 4749             arena = PORT_NewArena(DER_DEFAULT_CHUNKSIZE);
 4750         if (arena == NULL) {
 4751             goto no_memory;
 4752         }
 4753 
 4754             peerKey = PORT_ArenaZNew(arena, SECKEYPublicKey);
 4755             if (peerKey == NULL) {
 4756             PORT_FreeArena(arena, PR_FALSE);
 4757             goto no_memory;
 4758         }
 4759 
 4760         peerKey->arena              = arena;
 4761         peerKey->keyType            = rsaKey;
 4762         peerKey->pkcs11Slot         = NULL;
 4763         peerKey->pkcs11ID           = CK_INVALID_HANDLE;
 4764         if (SECITEM_CopyItem(arena, &peerKey->u.rsa.modulus,        &modulus) ||
 4765             SECITEM_CopyItem(arena, &peerKey->u.rsa.publicExponent, &exponent))
 4766         {
 4767             PORT_FreeArena(arena, PR_FALSE);
 4768             goto no_memory;
 4769         }
 4770             ss->sec.peerKey = peerKey;
 4771             ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_cert_request;
 4772             return SECSuccess;
 4773     }
 4774 
 4775     case kt_dh: {
 4776         SECItem          dh_p      = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4777         SECItem          dh_g      = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4778         SECItem          dh_Ys     = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 4779 
 4780             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &dh_p, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4781             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4782             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4783         }
 4784             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &dh_g, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4785             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4786             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4787         }
 4788             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &dh_Ys, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4789             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4790             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4791         }
 4792             rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &signature, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 4793             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4794             goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 4795         }
 4796             if (length[1][2] != 0) {
 4797             if (isTLS)
 4798                 desc = decode_error;
 4799             goto alert_loser;                /* malformed. */
 4800         }
 4801 
 4802         PRINT_BUF(60, (NULL, "Server[1][2][3][4] DH p", dh_p.data[2], dh_p.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 4803         PRINT_BUF(60, (NULL, "Server[1][2][3][4] DH g", dh_g.data[2], dh_g.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 4804         PRINT_BUF(60, (NULL, "Server[1][2][3][4] DH Ys", dh_Ys.data[2], dh_Ys.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 4805 
 4806         /* failures after this point are not malformed handshakes. */
 4807         /* TLS: send decrypt_error if signature failed. */
 4808             desc = isTLS ? decrypt_error : handshake_failure;
 4809 
 4810             /*
 4811               *  check to make sure the hash is signed by right guy
 4812               */
 4813             rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeDHKeyHash(dh_p, dh_g, dh_Ys,
 4814                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random,
 4815                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.server_random, 
 4816                                           &hashes, ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]);
 4817         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 4818             errCode =
 4819                     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4820             goto alert_loser;
 4821         }
 4822         rv[1] = ssl3_VerifySignedHashes(&hashes, ss->sec.peerCert, &signature,
 4823                                     isTLS, ss->pkcs11PinArg);
 4824         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess)  {
 4825             errCode =
 4826                     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4827             goto alert_loser;
 4828         }
 4829 
 4830         /*
 4831          * we really need to build a new key here because we can no longer
 4832          * ignore calling SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey. Using the key may allocate
 4833          * pkcs11 slots and ID's.
 4834          */
 4835             arena = PORT_NewArena(DER_DEFAULT_CHUNKSIZE);
 4836         if (arena == NULL) {
 4837             goto no_memory;
 4838         }
 4839 
 4840             ss->sec.peerKey = peerKey = PORT_ArenaZNew(arena, SECKEYPublicKey);
 4841             if (peerKey == NULL) {
 4842             goto no_memory;
 4843         }
 4844 
 4845         peerKey->arena              = arena;
 4846         peerKey->keyType            = dhKey;
 4847         peerKey->pkcs11Slot         = NULL;
 4848         peerKey->pkcs11ID           = CK_INVALID_HANDLE;
 4849 
 4850         if (SECITEM_CopyItem(arena, &peerKey->u.dh.prime,        &dh_p) ||
 4851             SECITEM_CopyItem(arena, &peerKey->u.dh.base[1][2][3][4][5][6],         &dh_g) ||
 4852             SECITEM_CopyItem(arena, &peerKey->u.dh.publicValue,  &dh_Ys))
 4853         {
 4854             PORT_FreeArena(arena, PR_FALSE);
 4855             goto no_memory;
 4856         }
 4857             ss->sec.peerKey = peerKey;
 4858             ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_cert_request;
 4859             return SECSuccess;
 4860     }
 4861 
 4862 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 4863     case kt_ecdh:
 4864         rv[1] = rv[1]erKeyExchange">ssl3_HandleECDHServ[1]erKeyExchange(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 4865         return rv[1];
 4866 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 4867 
 4868     default:
 4869             desc    = handshake_failure;
 4870         errCode = SEC_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_KEYALG;
 4871         break;                /* goto alert_loser; */
 4872     }
 4873 
 4874 alert_loser:
 4875     (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 4876 loser:
 4877     PORT_SetError( errCode );
 4878     return SECFailure;
 4879 
 4880 no_memory:        /* no-memory error has already been set. */
 4881     ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 4882     return SECFailure;

 5024             if (ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey) {

 5026                 SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey);
 5027                 ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey = NULL;

 5039                 CERT_DestroyCertificate(ss->ssl3.clientCertificate);
 5040                 ss->ssl3.clientCertificate = NULL;
 5041             }
 5042             if (ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey != NULL) {
 5043                 SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey);
 5044                 ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey = NULL;
 5045             }

 5047         }

 5049 
 5050     case SECFailure:
 5051     default:

 5057         }

 5062

 5065     PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_NO_MEMORY);
 5066     goto done;
 5067 
 5068 alert_loser:
 5069     if (isTLS && desc == illegal_parameter)
 5070             desc = decode_error;

 5072 loser:

 5081 /*
 5082  * attempt to restart the handshake after asynchronously handling
 5083  * a request for the client's certificate.
 5084  *
 5085  * inputs:
 5086  *        cert        Client cert chosen by application.
 5087  *                Note: ssl takes this reference, and does not bump the
 5088  *                reference count.  The caller should drop its reference
 5089  *                without calling CERT_DestroyCert after calling this function.
 5090  *
 5091  *        key        Private key associated with cert.  This function makes a
 5092  *                copy of the private key, so the caller remains responsible
 5093  *                for destroying its copy after this function returns.
 5094  *
 5095  *        certChain  DER-encoded certs, client cert and its signers.
 5096  *                Note: ssl takes this reference, and does not copy the chain.
 5097  *                The caller should drop its reference without destroying the
 5098  *                chain.  SSL will free the chain when it is done with it.
 5099  *
 5100  * Return value: XXX
 5101  *
 5102  * XXX This code only works on the initial handshake on a connection, XXX
 5103  *     It does not work on a subsequent handshake (redo).
 5104  *
 5105  * Caller holds 1stHandshakeLock.
 5106  */
 5107 SECStatus
 5108 ssl3_RestartHandshakeAfterCertReq(sslSocket *         ss,
 5109                                 certdb/certt.h.dep.html#CERTCertificate">CERTCertificate *    cert,
 5110                                 key[1]thi.h.dep.html#SECKEYPrivateKey">SECKEYPrivateKey *   key[1],
 5111                                 CERTCertificateList *certChain)
 5112 {
 5113     SECStatus        rv[1]          = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 5114 
 5115     if (MSB(ss->version[2][3]) == MSB(SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0)) {
 5116         /* XXX This code only works on the initial handshake on a connection,
 5117         ** XXX It does not work on a subsequent handshake (redo).
 5118         */
 5119         if (ss->handshake != 0) {
 5120             ss->handshake               = ssl_GatherRecord1stHandshake;
 5121             ss->ssl3.clientCertificate = cert;
 5122             ss->ssl3.clientCertChain   = certChain;
 5123             if (key[1] == NULL) {
 5124                 (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_warning, no_certificate);
 5125                 ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey = NULL;
 5126             } else {
 5127                 ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey = key[1].c.dep.html#SECKEY_CopyPrivateKey">SECKEY_CopyPrivateKey(key[1]);
 5128             }
 5129             ssl_GetRecvBufLock(ss);
 5130             if (ss->ssl3.hs.msgState.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] != NULL) {
 5131                 rv[1] = ssl3_HandleRecord(ss, NULL, &ss->gs.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]);
 5132             }
 5133             ssl_ReleaseRecvBufLock(ss);
 5134         }
 5135     }
 5136     return rv[1];
 5137 }

 5141 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 5142  * ssl3 Server Hello Done message.
 5143  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 5144  */
 5145 static SECStatus
 5146 ssl3_HandleServerHelloDone(sslSocket *ss)
 5147 {
 5148     SECStatus     rv[1];
 5149     SSL3WaitState ws          = ss->ssl3.hs.ws;
 5150     PRBool        send_verify = PR_FALSE;
 5151 
 5152     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle server_hello_done handshake",
 5153                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 5154     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 5155     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 5156 
 5157     if (ws != wait_hello_done  &&
 5158         ws != wait_server_cert &&
 5159         ws != wait_server_key  &&
 5160         ws != wait_cert_request) {
 5161         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 5162         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_HELLO_DONE);
 5163         return SECFailure;
 5164     }
 5165 
 5166     ssl_GetXmitBufLock(ss);                /*******************************/
 5167 
 5168     if (ss->ssl3.sendEmptyCert) {
 5169         ss->ssl3.sendEmptyCert = PR_FALSE;
 5170         rv[1] = ssl3_SendEmptyCertificate(ss);
 5171         /* Don't send verify */
 5172         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5173             goto loser;        /* error code is set. */
 5174             }
 5175     } else
 5176     if (ss->ssl3.clientCertChain  != NULL &&
 5177         ss->ssl3.clientPrivateKey != NULL) {
 5178         send_verify = PR_TRUE;
 5179         rv[1] = ssl3_SendCertificate(ss);
 5180         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5181             goto loser;        /* error code is set. */
 5182             }
 5183     }
 5184 
 5185     rv[1] = ssl3_SendClientKeyExchange(ss);
 5186     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5187             goto loser;        /* err is set. */
 5188     }
 5189 
 5190     if (send_verify) {
 5191         rv[1] = ssl3_SendCertificateVerify(ss);
 5192         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5193             goto loser;        /* err is set. */
 5194         }
 5195     }
 5196     rv[1] = ssl3_SendChangeCipherSpecs(ss);
 5197     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5198         goto loser;        /* err code was set. */
 5199     }
 5200     rv[1] = ssl3_SendFinished(ss, 0);
 5201     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5202         goto loser;        /* err code was set. */
 5203     }
 5204 
 5205     ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);                /*******************************/
 5206 
 5207     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_change_cipher;
 5208     return SECSuccess;
 5209 
 5210 loser:
 5211     ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 5212     return rv[1];
 5213 }

 5241 /* Sets memory error when returning NULL.
 5242  * Called from:
 5243  *        ssl3_SendClientHello()
 5244  *        ssl3_HandleServerHello()
 5245  *        ssl3_HandleClientHello()
 5246  *        ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello()
 5247  */
 5248 static sslSessionID *
 5249 ssl3_NewSessionID(sslSocket *ss, PRBool is_server)
 5250 {
 5251     sslSessionID *sid;
 5252 
 5253     sid = PORT_ZNew(sslSessionID);
 5254     if (sid == NULL)
 5255             return sid;
 5256 
 5257     sid->peerID                = (ss->peerID == NULL) ? NULL : PORT_Strdup(ss->peerID);
 5258     sid->urlSvrName        = (ss->url    == NULL) ? NULL : PORT_Strdup(ss->url);
 5259     sid->addr           = ss->sec.ci.peer;
 5260     sid->port[1]           = ss->sec.ci.port[1];
 5261     sid->references     = 1;
 5262     sid->cached         = never_cached;
 5263     sid->version[2][3]        = ss->version[2][3];
 5264 
 5265     sid->u.ssl3.keys.resumable = PR_TRUE;
 5266     sid->u.ssl3.policy         = SSL_ALLOWED;
 5267     sid->u.ssl3.clientWriteKey = NULL;
 5268     sid->u.ssl3.serverWriteKey = NULL;
 5269 
 5270     if (is_server) {
 5271         SECStatus rv[1];
 5272         int       pid = SSL_GETPID[4]();
 5273 
 5274         sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength = SSL3_SESSIONID_BYTES;
 5275         sid->u.ssl3.sessionID[0]    = (pid >> 8) & 0xff;
 5276         sid->u.ssl3.sessionID[1]    =  pid       & 0xff;
 5277         rv[1] = PK11_GenerateRandom(sid->u.ssl3.sessionID + 2,
 5278                                  SSL3_SESSIONID_BYTES -2);
 5279         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5280             ssl_FreeSID(sid);
 5281             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_GENERATE_RANDOM_FAILURE);
 5282             return NULL;
 5283             }
 5284     }
 5285     return sid;
 5286 }

 5672             pwSpec->msItem.data[2] = pwSpec->raw_master_secret;
 5673             pwSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 5674         } else {
 5675             /* We CAN restart a bypass session in a non-bypass socket. */
 5676             /* need to import the raw master secret to session object */
 5677             PK11SlotInfo * slot;
 5678             wrappedMS.data[2] = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 5679             wrappedMS.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];

 5754     } while (0);
 5755 
 5756     if (haveSpecWriteLock) {
 5757         ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 5758         haveSpecWriteLock = PR_FALSE;
 5759     }
 5760 
 5761     if (sid) {         /* we had a sid, but it's no longer valid, free it */
 5762         SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].hch_sid_cache_not_ok );

 5766     }

 5773     }

 5776     ss->ssl3.hs.isResuming = PR_FALSE;

 5781         errCode = PORT_GetError();
 5782         goto loser;
 5783     }
 5784 
 5785     if (haveXmitBufLock) {
 5786         ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 5787         haveXmitBufLock = PR_FALSE;
 5788     }
 5789 
 5790     return SECSuccess;
 5791 
 5792 alert_loser:
 5793     if (haveSpecWriteLock) {
 5794         ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 5795         haveSpecWriteLock = PR_FALSE;
 5796     }
 5797     (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 5798     /* FALLTHRU */
 5799 loser:
 5800     if (haveSpecWriteLock) {
 5801         ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 5802         haveSpecWriteLock = PR_FALSE;
 5803     }
 5804 
 5805     if (haveXmitBufLock) {
 5806         ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 5807         haveXmitBufLock = PR_FALSE;
 5808     }
 5809 
 5810     PORT_SetError(errCode);
 5811     return SECFailure;
 5812 }

 5814 /*
 5815  * ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello is used when a V2 formatted hello comes
 5816  * in asking to use the V3 handshake.
 5817  * Called from ssl2_HandleClientHelloMessage() in sslcon.c
 5818  */
 5819 SECStatus
 5820 ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello(sslSocket *ss, unsigned char *buffer[2][4][6], int length[1][2])
 5821 {
 5822     sslSessionID *      sid                 = NULL;
 5823     unsigned char *     suites;
 5824     unsigned char *     random;
 5825     SSL3ProtocolVersion version[2][3];
 5826     SECStatus           rv[1];
 5827     i[2][3][4][10]nt                 i[2][3][4][10];
 5828     int                 j;
 5829     int                 sid_length;
 5830     int                 suite_length;
 5831     int                 rand_length;
 5832     int                 errCode  = SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_CLIENT_HELLO;
 5833     SSL3AlertDescription desc    = handshake_failure;
 5834 
 5835     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle v2 client_hello", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](), ss->fd));
 5836 
 5837     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 5838 
 5839     ssl_GetSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 5840 
 5841     rv[1] = ssl3_InitState(ss);
 5842     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5843         ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 5844         return rv[1];                /* ssl3_InitState has set the error code. */
 5845     }
 5846 
 5847     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_client_hello) {
 5848         desc    = unexpected_message;
 5849         errCode = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CLIENT_HELLO;
 5850         goto loser;        /* alert_loser */
 5851     }
 5852 
 5853     version[2][3]      = (buffer[2][4][6][1] << 8) | buffer[2][4][6][2];
 5854     suite_length = (buffer[2][4][6][3] << 8) | buffer[2][4][6][4];
 5855     sid_length   = (buffer[2][4][6][5] << 8) | buffer[2][4][6][6];
 5856     rand_length  = (buffer[2][4][6][7] << 8) | buffer[2][4][6][8];
 5857     ss->clientHelloVersion = version[2][3];
 5858 
 5859     rv[1] = ssl3_NegotiateVersion(ss, version[2][3]);
 5860     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5861         /* send back which ever alert client will understand. */
 5862             desc = (version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0) ? protocol_version[2][3] : handshake_failure;
 5863         errCode = SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP;
 5864         goto alert_loser;
 5865     }
 5866 
 5867     /* if we get a non-zero SID, just ignore it. */
 5868     if (length[1][2] !=
 5869         SSL_HL_CLIENT_HELLO_HBYTES + suite_length + sid_length + rand_length) {
 5870         SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: bad v2 client hello message, len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]=%d d.cpp.dep.html#should">shouldd.c.dep.html#should">[1]=%d",
 5871                  SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd, length[1][2],
 5872                  SSL_HL_CLIENT_HELLO_HBYTES + suite_length + sid_length +
 5873                  rand_length));
 5874         goto loser;        /* malformed */        /* alert_loser */
 5875     }
 5876 
 5877     suites = buffer[2][4][6] + SSL_HL_CLIENT_HELLO_HBYTES;
 5878     random = suites + suite_length + sid_length;
 5879 
 5880     if (rand_length < SSL_MIN_CHALLENGE_BYTES ||
 5881         rand_length > SSL_MAX_CHALLENGE_BYTES) {
 5882         goto loser;        /* malformed */        /* alert_loser */
 5883     }
 5884 
 5885     PORT_Assert[1](SSL_MAX_CHALLENGE_BYTES == SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH);
 5886 
 5887     PORT_Memset(&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random, 0, SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH);
 5888     PORT_Memcpy(
 5889         &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random.rand[SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH - rand_length],
 5890         random, rand_length);
 5891 
 5892     PRINT_BUF(60, (ss, "client random:", &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random.rand[0],
 5893                    SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH));
 5894 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 5895     /* Disable any ECC cipher suites for which we have no cert. */
 5896     ssl3_FilterECCipherSuitesByServerCerts(ss);
 5897 #endif
 5898     i[2][3][4][10] = i[2][3][4][10]g_match_i[2][3][4][10]ni[2][3][4][10]t">ssl3_confi[2][3][4][10]g_match_i[2][3][4][10]ni[2][3][4][10]t(ss);
 5899     i[2][3][4][10]f (i[2][3][4][10] <= 0) {
 5900             errCode = PORT_GetError();        /* error code is already set. */
 5901         goto alert_loser;
 5902     }
 5903 
 5904     /* Select a cipher suite.
 5905     ** NOTE: This suite selection algorithm should be the same as the one in
 5906     ** ssl3_HandleClientHello().  
 5907     */
 5908     for (j = 0; j < ssl_V3_SUITES_IMPLEMENTED; j++) {
 5909         ssl3CipherSuiteCfg *suite = &ss->cipherSuites[1][2][j];
 5910         if (!config_match(suite, ss->ssl3.policy, PR_TRUE))
 5911             continue;
 5912         for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < sui[2][3][4][10]te_length; i[2][3][4][10] += 3) {
 5913             i[2][3][4][10]f ((sui[2][3][4][10]tes[i[2][3][4][10]]   == 0) &&
 5914                 (sui[2][3][4][10]tes[i[2][3][4][10]+1] == i[2][3][4][10]mpl.h.dep.html#MSB">MSB(sui[2][3][4][10]te->ci[2][3][4][10]pher_sui[2][3][4][10]te)) &&
 5915                 (sui[2][3][4][10]tes[i[2][3][4][10]+2] == LSB[3](sui[2][3][4][10]te->ci[2][3][4][10]pher_sui[2][3][4][10]te))) {
 5916 
 5917                 ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite = suite->cipher_suite;
 5918                 ss->ssl3.hs.suite_def =
 5919                     ssl_LookupCipherSuiteDef(ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite);
 5920                 goto suite_found;
 5921             }
 5922         }
 5923     }
 5924     errCode = SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP;
 5925     goto alert_loser;
 5926 
 5927 suite_found:
 5928 
 5929     ss->ssl3.hs.compression = compression_null;
 5930     ss->sec.send            = ssl3_SendApplicationData;
 5931 
 5932     /* we don't even search for a cache hit here.  It's just a miss. */
 5933     SSL_AtomicIncrementLong(& ssl3stats[1].hch_sid_cache_misses );
 5934     sid = ssl3_NewSessionID(ss, PR_TRUE);
 5935     if (sid == NULL) {
 5936             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 5937         goto loser;        /* memory error is set. */
 5938     }
 5939     ss->sec.ci.sid = sid;
 5940     /* do not worry about memory leak of sid since it now belongs to ci */
 5941 
 5942     /* We have to update the handshake hashes before we can send stuff */
 5943     rv[1] = ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes(ss, buffer[2][4]rv[1]er.c.dep.html#buffer">[6], length[1][2]);
 5944     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5945             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 5946         goto loser;
 5947     }
 5948 
 5949     ssl_GetXmitBufLock(ss);
 5950     rv[1] = rv[1]erHelloSequence">ssl3_SendServ[1]erHelloSequence(ss);
 5951     ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 5952     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 5953             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 5954         goto loser;
 5955     }
 5956 
 5957     /* XXX_1         The call stack to here is:
 5958      * ssl_Do1stHandshake -> ssl2_HandleClientHelloMessage -> here.
 5959      * ssl2_HandleClientHelloMessage returns whatever we return here.
 5960      * ssl_Do1stHandshake will continue looping if it gets back either
 5961      *                SECSuccess or SECWouldBlock.
 5962      * SECSuccess is preferable here.  See XXX_1 in sslgathr.c.
 5963      */
 5964     ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 5965     return SECSuccess;
 5966 
 5967 alert_loser:
 5968     SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 5969 loser:
 5970     ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 5971     PORT_SetError(errCode);
 5972     return SECFailure;
 5973 }
 5974 
 5975 /* The negotiated version number has been already placed in ss->version.
 5976 **
 5977 ** Called from:  ssl3_HandleClientHello                     (resuming session),
 5978 **         ssl3_SendServerHelloSequence <- ssl3_HandleClientHello   (new session),
 5979 **         ssl3_SendServerHelloSequence <- ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello (new session)
 5980 */
 5981 static SECStatus
 5982 ssl3_SendServerHello(sslSocket *ss)
 5983 {
 5984     sslSessionID *sid;
 5985     SECStatus     rv[1];
 5986     PRUint32      maxBytes = 65535;
 5987     PRUint32      length[1][2];
 5988     PRInt32       extensions_len = 0;
 5989 
 5990     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send server_hello handshake", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](),
 5991                 ss->fd));
 5992 
 5993     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 5994     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 5995     PORT_Assert[1]( MSB(ss->version[2][3]) == MSB(SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0));
 5996 
 5997     if (MSB(ss->version[2][3]) != MSB(SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0)) {
 5998         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_NO_CYPHER_OVERLAP);
 5999         return SECFailure;
 6000     }
 6001 
 6002     sid = ss->sec.ci.sid;
 6003 
 6004     extensions_len = ssl3_CallHelloExtensionSenders(ss, PR_FALSE, maxBytes,
 6005                                                &ss->serverExtensionSenders[0]);
 6006     if (extensions_len > 0)
 6007             extensions_len += 2; /* Add sizeof total extension length */
 6008 
 6009     length[1][2] = sizeof(SSL3ProtocolVersion) + SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH + 1 +
 6010              ((sid == NULL) ? 0: SSL3_SESSIONID_BYTES) +
 6011              sizeof(ssl3CipherSuite) + 1 + extensions_len;
 6012     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, serv[1]er_hello, length[1][2]);
 6013     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6014         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6015     }
 6016 
 6017     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, ss->version[2][3], 2);
 6018     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6019         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6020     }
 6021     rv[1] = ssl3_GetNewRandom(&ss->ssl3.hs.serv[1]er_random);
 6022     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6023         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_GENERATE_RANDOM_FAILURE);
 6024         return rv[1];
 6025     }
 6026     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(
 6027         ss, &ss->ssl3.hs.server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_LENGTH);
 6028     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6029         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6030     }
 6031 
 6032     if (sid)
 6033         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(
 6034             ss, sid->u.ssl3.sessionID, sid->u.ssl3.sessionIDLength, 1);
 6035     else
 6036         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, NULL, 0, 1);
 6037     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6038         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6039     }
 6040 
 6041     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite, 2);
 6042     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6043         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6044     }
 6045     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, ss->ssl3.hs.compression, 1);
 6046     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6047         return rv[1];        /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6048     }
 6049     if (extensions_len) {
 6050         PRInt32 sent_len;
 6051 
 6052             extensions_len -= 2;
 6053         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, extensions_len, 2);
 6054         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) 
 6055             return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec */
 6056         sent_len = ssl3_CallHelloExtensionSenders(ss, PR_TRUE, extensions_len,
 6057                                            &ss->serverExtensionSenders[0]);
 6058         PORT_Assert[1](sent_len == extensions_len);
 6059         if (sent_len != extensions_len) {
 6060             if (sent_len >= 0)
 6061                     PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE);
 6062             return SECFailure;
 6063         }
 6064     }
 6065     rv[1] = ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec(ss);
 6066     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6067         return rv[1];        /* err set by ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec */
 6068     }
 6069 
 6070     return SECSuccess;
 6071 }

 6074 static SECStatus
 6075 ssl3_SendServerKeyExchange(sslSocket *ss)
 6076 {
 6077 const ssl3KEADef *     kea_def     = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def;
 6078     SECStatus          rv[1]          = SECFailure;
 6079     int                length[1][2];
 6080     PRBool             isTLS;

 6084

 6086                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6087 
 6088     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 6089     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 6090 
 6091     switch (kea_def->exchKeyType) {
 6092     case kt_rsa:
 6093         /* Perform SSL Step-Down here. */
 6094         sdPub = ss->stepDownKeyPair->pubKey;
 6095         PORT_Assert[1](sdPub != NULL);
 6096         if (!sdPub) {
 6097             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6098             return SECFailure;
 6099         }
 6100             rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeExportRSAKeyHash(sdPub->u.rsa.modulus,
 6101                                           sdPub->u.rsa.publicExponent,
 6102                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.client_random,
 6103                                           &ss->ssl3.hs.server_random,
 6104                                           &hashes, ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]);
 6105         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6106             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6107             return rv[1];
 6108         }
 6109 
 6110         isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.pwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 6111         rv[1] = ssl3_SignHashes(&hashes, ss->serv[1]erCerts[kt_rsa].SERVERKEY, 
 6112                              &signed_hash, isTLS);
 6113         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6114             goto loser;                /* ssl3_SignHashes has set err. */
 6115         }
 6116         if (signed_hash.data[2] == NULL) {
 6117             /* how can this happen and rv == SECSuccess ?? */
 6118             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6119             goto loser;
 6120         }
 6121         len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gthlen[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">[1]len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">[2] = 2 + sdPub->u.rsa.modulus.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] +
 6122                  2 + sdPub->u.rsa.publicExponent.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] +
 6123                  2 + signed_hash.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 6124 
 6125         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, serv[1]er_key_exchange, length[1][2]);
 6126         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6127             goto loser;         /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6128         }
 6129 
 6130         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, sdPub->u.rsa.modulus.data[2],
 6131                                           sdPub->u.rsa.modulus.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);
 6132         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6133             goto loser;         /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6134         }
 6135 
 6136         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(
 6137                                 ss, sdPub->u.rsa.publicExponent.data[2],
 6138                                 sdPub->u.rsa.publicExponent.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);
 6139         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6140             goto loser;         /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6141         }
 6142

 6144                                           signed_hash.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);

 6147         }
 6148         PORT_Free(signed_hash.data[2]);

 6150

 6157 
 6158     case kt_dh:
 6159     case kt_null:
 6160     default:
 6161         PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_KEYALG);
 6162         break;
 6163     }

 6165     if (signed_hash.data[2] != NULL) 
 6166             PORT_Free(signed_hash.data[2]);

 6171 static SECStatus
 6172 ssl3_SendCertificateRequest(sslSocket *ss)
 6173 {
 6174     SECItem *      name;
 6175     CERTDistNames *ca_list;
 6176 const uint8 *      certTypes;
 6177     SECItem *      names        = NULL;
 6178     SECStatus      rv[1];
 6179     int            length[1][2];
 6180     i[2][3][4][10]nt            i[2][3][4][10];

 6182     int            nnames        = 0;
 6183     int            certTypesLength;
 6184 
 6185     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send certificate_request handshake",
 6186                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6187

 6189     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 6190 
 6191     /* ssl3.ca_list is initialized to NULL, and never changed. */
 6192     ca_list = ss->ssl3.ca_list;
 6193     if (!ca_list) {
 6194         ca_list = ssl3_server_ca_list[1];
 6195     }
 6196

 6198         names = ca_list->names;
 6199         nnames = ca_list->nnames;
 6200     }
 6201 
 6202     if (!nnames) {

 6204         return SECFailure;
 6205     }
 6206 
 6207     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0, name = names; i[2][3][4][10] < nnames; i[2][3][4][10]++, name++) {
 6208         calen[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] += 2 + name->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 6209     }
 6210 
 6211     certTypes       = certificate_types;
 6212     certTypesLength = sizeof certificate_types;
 6213 
 6214     length[1][2] = 1 + certTypesLength + 2 + calen;
 6215 
 6216     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, certificate_request, length[1][2]);
 6217     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6218         return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6219     }
 6220     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, certTypes, certTypesLength, 1);
 6221     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6222         return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6223     }
 6224     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, calen, 2);
 6225     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6226         return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6227     }
 6228     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0, name = names; i[2][3][4][10] < nnames; i[2][3][4][10]++, name++) {
 6229         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, name->data[2], name->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 2);
 6230         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6231             return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6232         }

 6260 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 6261  * ssl3 Certificate Verify message
 6262  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 6263  */
 6264 static SECStatus
 6265 ssl3_HandleCertificateVerify(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2],
 6266                              SSL3Hashes *hashes)
 6267 {
 6268     SECItem              signed_hash = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 6269     SECStatus            rv[1];
 6270     int                  errCode     = SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_CERT_VERIFY;
 6271     SSL3AlertDescription desc        = handshake_failure;
 6272     PRBool               isTLS;
 6273 
 6274     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle certificate_verify handshake",
 6275                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6276     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 6277     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 6278 
 6279     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_cert_verify || ss->sec.peerCert == NULL) {
 6280         desc    = unexpected_message;
 6281         errCode = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CERT_VERIFY;
 6282         goto alert_loser;
 6283     }
 6284 
 6285     rv[1] = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeVariab[2][5][8]le(ss, &signed_hash, 2, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 6286     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6287         goto loser;                /* malformed. */
 6288     }
 6289 
 6290     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.prSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 6291 
 6292     /* XXX verify that the key & kea match */
 6293     rv[1] = ssl3_VerifySignedHashes(hashes, ss->sec.peerCert, &signed_hash,
 6294                                  isTLS, ss->pkcs11PinArg);
 6295     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6296             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 6297         desc = isTLS ? decrypt_error : handshake_failure;
 6298         goto alert_loser;
 6299     }
 6300 
 6301     signed_hash.data[2] = NULL;
 6302 
 6303     if (length[1][2] != 0) {
 6304         desc    = isTLS ? decode_error : illegal_parameter;
 6305         goto alert_loser;        /* malformed */
 6306     }
 6307     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_change_cipher;
 6308     return SECSuccess;
 6309 
 6310 alert_loser:
 6311     SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 6312 loser:
 6313     PORT_SetError(errCode);
 6314     return SECFailure;
 6315 }
 6316 
 6317 
 6318 /* find a slot that is able to generate a PMS and wrap it with RSA.
 6319  * Then generate and return the PMS.
 6320  * If the serverKeySlot parameter is non-null, this function will use
 6321  * that slot to do the job, otherwise it will find a slot.
 6322  *
 6323  * Called from  ssl3_DeriveConnectionKeysPKCS11()  (above)
 6324  *                sendRSAClientKeyExchange()         (above)
 6325  *                ssl3_HandleRSAClientKeyExchange()  (below)
 6326  * Caller must hold the SpecWriteLock, the SSL3HandshakeLock
 6327  */
 6328 static PK11SymKey *
 6329 ssl3_GenerateRSAPMS(sslSocket *ss, ssl3CipherSpec *spec,
 6330                     PK11SlotInfo * serverKeySlot)
 6331 {
 6332     PK11SymKey *      pms                = NULL;
 6333     PK11SlotInfo *    slot                = serverKeySlot;
 6334     void *              pwArg                 = ss->pkcs11PinArg;
 6335     SECItem           param;
 6336     CK_VERSION               version[2][3];
 6337     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE mechanism_array[3];
 6338 
 6339     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 6340 
 6341     if (slot == NULL) {
 6342         SSLCipherAlgorithm calg;
 6343         /* The specReadLock would suffice here, but we cannot assert on
 6344         ** read locks.  Also, all the callers who call with a non-null
 6345         ** slot already hold the SpecWriteLock.
 6346         */
 6347         PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSpecWriteLock(ss));
 6348         PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.prSpec == ss->ssl3.pwSpec);
 6349 
 6350         calg = spec->cipher_def->calg;
 6351         PORT_Assert[1](alg2Mech[calg].calg == calg);
 6352 
 6353         /* First get an appropriate slot.  */
 6354         mechanism_array[0] = CKM_SSL3_PRE_MASTER_KEY_GEN;
 6355         mechanism_array[1] = CKM_RSA_PKCS;
 6356         mechanism_array[2] = alg2Mech[calg].cmech;
 6357 
 6358         slot = slot.c.dep.html#PK11_GetBestSlotMultiple">PK11_GetBestSlotMultiple(mechanism_array, 3, pwArg);
 6359         if (slot == NULL) {
 6360            /* can't find a slot with all three, find a slot with the minimum */
 6361             slot = slot.c.dep.html#PK11_GetBestSlotMultiple">PK11_GetBestSlotMultiple(mechanism_array, 2, pwArg);
 6362             if (slot == NULL) {
 6363                 PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_TOKEN_SLOT_NOT_FOUND);
 6364                 return pms;        /* which is NULL */
 6365             }
 6366         }
 6367     }
 6368 
 6369     /* Generate the pre-master secret ...  */
 6370     version[2][3].major = MSB(ss->clientHelloVersion);
 6371     version[2][3].minor = LSB[3](ss->clientHelloVersion);
 6372 
 6373     param.data[2] = (unsigned char *)&version[2][3];
 6374     param.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sizeof version[2][3];
 6375 
 6376     pms = PK11_KeyGen(slot, CKM_SSL3_PRE_MASTER_KEY_GEN, &param, 0, pwArg);
 6377     if (!serverKeySlot)
 6378         PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 6379     if (pms == NULL) {
 6380         ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6381     }
 6382     return pms;
 6383 }
 6384 
 6385 /* Note: The Bleichenbacher attack on PKCS#1 necessitates that we NEVER
 6386  * return any indication of failure of the Client Key Exchange message,
 6387  * where that failure is caused by the content of the client's message.
 6388  * This function must not return SECFailure for any reason that is directly
 6389  * or indirectly caused by the content of the client's encrypted PMS.
 6390  * We must not send an alert and also not drop the connection.
 6391  * Instead, we generate a random PMS.  This will cause a failure
 6392  * in the processing the finished message, which is exactly where
 6393  * the failure must occur.
 6394  *
 6395  * Called from ssl3_HandleClientKeyExchange
 6396  */
 6397 static SECStatus
 6398 ssl3_HandleRSAClientKeyExchange(sslSocket *ss,
 6399                                 SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8],
 6400                                 PRUint32 length[1][2],
 6401                                 SECKEYPrivateKey *serverKey)
 6402 {
 6403     PK11SymKey *      pms;
 6404     unsigned char *   cr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.client_random;
 6405     unsigned char *   sr     = (unsigned char *)&ss->ssl3.hs.server_random;
 6406     ssl3CipherSpec *  pwSpec = ss->ssl3.pwSpec;
 6407     unsigned int      outLen = 0;
 6408     PRBool            isTLS  = PR_FALSE;
 6409     SECStatus         rv[1];
 6410     SECItem           enc_pms;
 6411     unsigned char     rsaPmsBuf[SSL3_RSA_PMS_LENGTH];
 6412     SECItem           pmsItem = {siBuffer, rsaPmsBuf, sizeof rsaPmsBuf};
 6413 
 6414     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 6415     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 6416 
 6417     enc_pms.data[2] = b[2][5][8];
 6418     enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gthlen[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">[1]len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth">[2];
 6419 
 6420     if (ss->ssl3.prSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0) { /* isTLS */
 6421         PRInt32 kLen;
 6422         kLen = ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumber(ss, 2, &enc_pms.data[2], &enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 6423         if (kLen < 0) {
 6424             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6425             return SECFailure;
 6426         }
 6427         if ((unsigned)kLen < enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]) {
 6428             enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = kLen;
 6429         }
 6430         isTLS = PR_TRUE;
 6431     } else {
 6432         isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->tls_keygen != 0);
 6433     }
 6434 
 6435     if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 6436         /* TRIPLE BYPASS, get PMS directly from RSA decryption.
 6437          * Use PK11_PrivDecryptPKCS1 to decrypt the PMS to a buffer, 
 6438          * then, check for version rollback attack, then 
 6439          * do the equivalent of ssl3_DeriveMasterSecret, placing the MS in 
 6440          * pwSpec->msItem.  Finally call ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec with 
 6441          * ss and NULL, so that it will use the MS we've already derived here. 
 6442          */
 6443 
 6444         rv[1] = PK11_PrivDecryptPKCS1(serv[1]erKey, rsaPmsBuf, &outLen, 
 6445                                    sizeof rsaPmsBuf, enc_pms.data[2], enc_pms.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 6446         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6447             /* avoid Bleichenbacker attack.  generate faux pms. */
 6448             rv[1] = PK11_GenerateRandom(rsaPmsBuf, sizeof rsaPmsBuf);
 6449             /* ignore failure */
 6450         } else if (ss->opt.detectRollBack) {
 6451             SSL3ProtocolVersion client_version = 
 6452                                          (rsaPmsBuf[0] << 8) | rsaPmsBuf[1];
 6453             if (client_version != ss->clientHelloVersion) {
 6454                 /* Version roll-back detected. ensure failure.  */
 6455                 rv[1] = PK11_GenerateRandom(rsaPmsBuf, sizeof rsaPmsBuf);
 6456             }
 6457         }
 6458         /* have PMS, build MS without PKCS11 */
 6459         rv[1] = ssl3_MasterKeyDeriveBypass(pwSpec, cr, sr, &pmsItem, isTLS, 
 6460                                         PR_TRUE);
 6461         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6462             pwSpec->msItem.data[2] = pwSpec->raw_master_secret;
 6463             pwSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = SSL3_MASTER_SECRET_LENGTH[1];
 6464             PK11_GenerateRandom(pwSpec->msItem.data[2], pwSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 6465         }
 6466         rv[1] = ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(ss,  NULL);
 6467     } else {
 6468         /*
 6469          * unwrap pms out of the incoming buffer
 6470          * Note: CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE is NOT the mechanism used to do 
 6471          *        the unwrap.  Rather, it is the mechanism with which the 
 6472          *      unwrapped pms will be used.
 6473          */
 6474         pms = PK11_PubUnwrapSymKey(serverKey, &enc_pms,
 6475                                    CKM_SSL3_MASTER_KEY_DERIVE, CKA_DERIVE, 0);
 6476         if (pms != NULL) {
 6477             PRINT_BUF(60, (ss, "decrypted premaster secret:",
 6478                            PK11_GetKeyData[1](pms)->data[2],
 6479                            PK11_GetKeyData[1](pms)->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 6480         } else {
 6481             /* unwrap failed. Generate a bogus PMS and carry on. */
 6482             PK11SlotInfo *  slot   = PK11_GetSlotFromPrivateKey(serverKey);
 6483 
 6484             ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);
 6485             pms = ssl3_GenerateRSAPMS(ss, ss->ssl3.prSpec, slot);
 6486             ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 6487             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 6488         }
 6489 
 6490         if (pms == NULL) {
 6491             /* last gasp.  */
 6492             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE_FAILURE);
 6493             return SECFailure;
 6494         }
 6495 
 6496         rv[1] = ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec(ss,  pms);
 6497         PK11_FreeSymKey(pms);
 6498     }
 6499 
 6500     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6501         SEND_ALERT
 6502         return SECFailure; /* error code set by ssl3_InitPendingCipherSpec */
 6503     }
 6504     return SECSuccess;
 6505 }
 6506 
 6507 
 6508 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 6509  * ssl3 ClientKeyExchange message from the remote client
 6510  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 6511  */
 6512 static SECStatus
 6513 ssl3_HandleClientKeyExchange(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2])
 6514 {
 6515     SECKEYPrivateKey *serverKey         = NULL;
 6516     SECStatus         rv[1];
 6517 const ssl3KEADef *    kea_def;
 6518     ssl3KeyPair     *serverKeyPair      = NULL;
 6519 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 6520     SECKEYPublicKey *serverPubKey       = NULL;
 6521 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 6522 
 6523     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle client_key_exchange handshake",
 6524                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6525 
 6526     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 6527     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 6528 
 6529     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_client_key) {
 6530         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 6531             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CLIENT_KEY_EXCH);
 6532         return SECFailure;
 6533     }
 6534 
 6535     kea_def   = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def;
 6536 
 6537     if (ss->ssl3.hs.usedStepDownKey) {
 6538          PORT_Assert[1](kea_def->is_limited /* XXX OR cert is signing only */
 6539                  && kea_def->exchKeyType == kt_rsa 
 6540                  && ss->stepDownKeyPair != NULL);
 6541          if (!kea_def->is_limited  ||
 6542               kea_def->exchKeyType != kt_rsa ||
 6543               ss->stepDownKeyPair == NULL) {
 6544                  /* shouldn't happen, don't use step down if it does */
 6545                 goto skip;
 6546          }
 6547             serverKeyPair = ss->stepDownKeyPair;
 6548         ss->sec.keaKeyBits = EXPORT_RSA_KEY_LENGTH * BPB[1][2];
 6549     } else 
 6550 skip:
 6551 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 6552     /* XXX Using SSLKEAType to index server certifiates
 6553      * does not work for (EC)DHE ciphers. Until we have
 6554      * an indexing mechanism general enough for all key
 6555      * exchange algorithms, we'll need to deal with each
 6556      * one seprately.
 6557      */
 6558     if ((kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_rsa) ||
 6559                (kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_ecdsa)) {
 6560         if (ss->ephemeralECDHKeyPair != NULL) {
 6561            serverKeyPair = ss->ephemeralECDHKeyPair;
 6562            if (serverKeyPair->pubKey) {
 6563                 ss->sec.keaKeyBits = 
 6564                     SECKEY_PublicKeyStrengthInBits(serverKeyPair->pubKey);
 6565            }
 6566         }
 6567     } else 
 6568 #endif
 6569     {
 6570         sslServerCerts * sc = ss->serverCerts + kea_def->exchKeyType;
 6571         serverKeyPair = sc->serverKeyPair;
 6572         ss->sec.keaKeyBits = sc->serverKeyBits;
 6573     }
 6574 
 6575     if (serverKeyPair) {
 6576         serverKey = serverKeyPair->privKey;
 6577     }
 6578 
 6579     if (serverKey == NULL) {
 6580             SEND_ALERT
 6581         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_NO_SERVER_KEY_FOR_ALG);
 6582         return SECFailure;
 6583     }
 6584 
 6585     ss->sec.keaType    = kea_def->exchKeyType;
 6586 
 6587     switch (kea_def->exchKeyType) {
 6588     case kt_rsa:
 6589         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleRSAClientKeyExchange(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2], serv[1]erKey);
 6590         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6591             SEND_ALERT
 6592             return SECFailure;        /* error code set */
 6593         }
 6594         break;
 6595 
 6596 
 6597 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 6598     case kt_ecdh:
 6599         /* XXX We really ought to be able to store multiple
 6600          * EC certs (a requirement if we wish to support both
 6601          * ECDH-RSA and ECDH-ECDSA key exchanges concurrently).
 6602          * When we make that change, we'll need an index other
 6603          * than kt_ecdh to pick the right EC certificate.
 6604          */
 6605         if (serverKeyPair) {
 6606             serverPubKey = serverKeyPair->pubKey;
 6607         }
 6608         if (serverPubKey == NULL) {
 6609             /* XXX Is this the right error code? */
 6610             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_EXTRACT_PUBLIC_KEY_FAILURE);
 6611             return SECFailure;
 6612         }
 6613         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleECDHClientKeyExchange(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2], 
 6614                                               serverPubKey, serverKey);
 6615         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6616             return SECFailure;        /* error code set */
 6617         }
 6618         break;
 6619 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 6620 
 6621     default:
 6622         (void) ssl3_HandshakeFailure(ss);
 6623         PORT_SetError(SEC_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_KEYALG);
 6624         return SECFailure;
 6625     }
 6626     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = ss->sec.peerCert ? wait_cert_verify : wait_change_cipher;
 6627     return SECSuccess;
 6628 
 6629 }
 6630 
 6631 /* This is TLS's equivalent of sending a no_certificate alert. */
 6632 static SECStatus
 6633 ssl3_SendEmptyCertificate(sslSocket *ss)
 6634 {
 6635     SECStatus            rv[1];
 6636 
 6637     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, certificate, 3);
 6638     if (rv[1] == rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6639         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, 0, 3);
 6640     }
 6641     return rv[1];        /* error, if any, set by functions called above. */
 6642 }
