 6706 /*
 6707  * Used by both client and server.
 6708  * Called from HandleServerHelloDone and from SendServerHelloSequence.
 6709  */
 6710 static SECStatus
 6711 ssl3_SendCertificate(sslSocket *ss)
 6712 {
 6713     SECStatus            rv[1];
 6714     CERTCertificateList *certChain;
 6715     int                  len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]                 = 0;
 6716     i[2][3][4][10]nt                  i[2][3][4][10];
 6717     SSL3KEAType          certIndex;
 6718 #ifdef NISCC_TEST
 6719     SECItem              fakeCert;
 6720     int                  ndex           = -1;
 6721 #endif
 6722 
 6723     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send certificate handshake",
 6724                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6725 
 6726     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 6727     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 6728 
 6729     if (ss->sec.localCert)
 6730             CERT_DestroyCertificate(ss->sec.localCert);
 6731     if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 6732         sslServerCerts * sc = NULL;
 6733 
 6734         /* XXX SSLKEAType isn't really a good choice for 
 6735          * indexing certificates (it breaks when we deal
 6736          * with (EC)DHE-* cipher suites. This hack ensures
 6737          * the RSA cert is picked for (EC)DHE-RSA.
 6738          * Revisit this when we add server side support
 6739          * for ECDHE-ECDSA or client-side authentication
 6740          * using EC certificates.
 6741          */
 6742         if ((ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_rsa) ||
 6743             (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_dhe_rsa)) {
 6744             certIndex = kt_rsa;
 6745         } else {
 6746             certIndex = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType;
 6747         }
 6748         sc                    = ss->serverCerts + certIndex;
 6749         certChain             = sc->serverCertChain;
 6750         ss->sec.authKeyBits   = sc->serverKeyBits;
 6751         ss->sec.authAlgorithm = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->signKeyType;
 6752         ss->sec.localCert     = CERT_DupCertificate(sc->serverCert);
 6753     } else {
 6754         certChain          = ss->ssl3.clientCertChain;
 6755         ss->sec.localCert = CERT_DupCertificate(ss->ssl3.clientCertificate);
 6756     }
 6757 
 6758 #ifdef NISCC_TEST
 6759     rv[1] = get_fake_cert(&fakeCert, &ndex);
 6760 #endif
 6761 
 6762     if (certChain) {
 6763         for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < certChai[2][3][4][10]n->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 6764 #ifdef NISCC_TEST
 6765             i[2][3][4][10]f (fakeCert.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > 0 && i[2][3][4][10] == ndex) {
 6766                 len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] += fakeCert.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 3;
 6767             } else {
 6768                 len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] += certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 3;
 6769             }
 6770 #else
 6771             len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] += certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 3;
 6772 #endif
 6773         }
 6774     }
 6775 
 6776     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, certificate, len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] + 3);
 6777     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6778         return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6779     }
 6780     rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeNumber(ss, len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 3);
 6781     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6782         return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6783     }
 6784     for (i[2][3][4][10] = 0; i[2][3][4][10] < certChai[2][3][4][10]n->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
 6785 #ifdef NISCC_TEST
 6786         i[2][3][4][10]f (fakeCert.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > 0 && i[2][3][4][10] == ndex) {
 6787             rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVariable(ss, fakeCert.data[2], fakeCert.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 
 6788                                               3);
 6789             SECITEM_FreeItem(&fakeCert, PR_FALSE);
 6790         } else {
 6791             rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVari[2][3][4][10]able(ss, certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].data[2],
 6792                                               certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 3);
 6793         }
 6794 #else
 6795         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeVari[2][3][4][10]able(ss, certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].data[2],
 6796                                           certChai[2][3][4][10]n->certs[i[2][3][4][10]].len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], 3);
 6797 #endif
 6798         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6799             return rv[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 6800         }
 6801     }
 6802 
 6803     return SECSuccess;
 6804 }
 6805 
 6806 /* This is used to delete the CA certificates in the peer certificate chain
 6807  * from the cert database after they've been validated.
 6808  */
 6809 static void
 6810 ssl3_CleanupPeerCerts(sslSocket *ss)
 6811 {
 6812     PRArenaPool * arena = ss->ssl3.peerCertArena;
 6813     ssl3CertNode *certs = (ssl3CertNode *)ss->ssl3.peerCertChain;
 6814 
 6815     for (; certs; certs = certs->next) {
 6816         certdb/stanpcertdb.c.dep.html#CERT_DestroyCertificate">CERT_DestroyCertificate(certs->cert);
 6817     }
 6818     if (arena) PORT_FreeArena(arena, PR_FALSE);
 6819     ss->ssl3.peerCertArena = NULL;
 6820     ss->ssl3.peerCertChain = NULL;
 6821 }
 6822 
 6823 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 6824  * ssl3 Certificate message.
 6825  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 6826  */
 6827 static SECStatus
 6828 ssl3_HandleCertificate(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2])
 6829 {
 6830     ssl3CertNode *   c[1][2];
 6831     ssl3CertNode *   certs         = NULL;
 6832     PRArenaPool *    arena         = NULL;
 6833     certdb/certt.h.dep.html#CERTCertificate">CERTCertificate *cert;
 6834     PRInt32          remaining  = 0;
 6835     PRInt32          size[4][8][9];
 6836     SECStatus        rv[1];
 6837     PRBool           isServer        = (PRBool)(!!ss->sec.isServer);
 6838     PRBool           trusted         = PR_FALSE;
 6839     PRBool           isTLS;
 6840     SSL3AlertDescription desc        = bad_certificate;
 6841     int              errCode    = SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_CERTIFICATE;
 6842     SECItem          certItem;
 6843 
 6844     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle certificate handshake",
 6845                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6846     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 6847     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 6848 
 6849     if ((ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_server_cert) &&
 6850         (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_client_cert)) {
 6851         desc    = unexpected_message;
 6852         errCode = SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CERTIFICATE;
 6853         goto alert_loser;
 6854     }
 6855 
 6856     if (ss->sec.peerCert != NULL) {
 6857         if (ss->sec.peerKey) {
 6858             seckey.c.dep.html#SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey">SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(ss->sec.peerKey);
 6859             ss->sec.peerKey = NULL;
 6860         }
 6861         CERT_DestroyCertificate(ss->sec.peerCert);
 6862         ss->sec.peerCert = NULL;
 6863     }
 6864 
 6865     ssl3_CleanupPeerCerts(ss);
 6866     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.prSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 6867 
 6868     /* It is reported that some TLS client sends a Certificate message
 6869     ** with a zero-length message body.  We'll treat that case like a
 6870     ** normal no_certificates message to maximize interoperability.
 6871     */
 6872     if (length[1][2]) {
 6873         remaining = b[2][5][8]er">ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumb[2][5][8]er(ss, 3, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 6874         if (remaining < 0)
 6875             goto loser;        /* fatal alert already sent by ConsumeHandshake. */
 6876         if ((PRUint32)remaining > length[1][2])
 6877             goto decode_loser;
 6878     }
 6879 
 6880     if (!remaining) {
 6881         if (!(isTLS && isServer))
 6882             goto alert_loser;
 6883             /* This is TLS's version of a no_certificate alert. */
 6884             /* I'm a server. I've requested a client cert. He hasn't got one. */
 6885         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleNoCertificate(ss);
 6886         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 6887             errCode = PORT_GetError();
 6888             goto loser;
 6889         }
 6890         goto cert_block;
 6891     }
 6892 
 6893     ss->ssl3.peerCertArena = arena = PORT_NewArena(DER_DEFAULT_CHUNKSIZE);
 6894     if ( arena == NULL ) {
 6895         goto loser;        /* don't send alerts on memory errors */
 6896     }
 6897 
 6898     /* First get the peer cert. */
 6899     remaining -= 3;
 6900     if (remaining < 0)
 6901         goto decode_loser;
 6902 
 6903     size[4][8][9] = b[2][5][8]er">ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumb[2][5][8]er(ss, 3, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 6904     if (size[4][8][9] <= 0)
 6905         goto loser;        /* fatal alert already sent by ConsumeHandshake. */
 6906 
 6907     if (remaining < size[4][8][9])
 6908         goto decode_loser;
 6909 
 6910     certItem.data[2] = b[2][5][8];
 6911     certItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = size[4][8][9];
 6912     b[2][5][8]      += size[4][8][9];
 6913     length[1][2] -= size[4][8][9];
 6914     remaining -= size[4][8][9];
 6915 
 6916     ss->sec.peerCert = CERT_NewTempCertificate[1](ss->dbHandle, &certItem, NULL,
 6917                                             PR_FALSE, PR_TRUE);
 6918     if (ss->sec.peerCert == NULL) {
 6919         /* We should report an alert if the cert was bad, but not if the
 6920          * problem was just some local problem, like memory error.
 6921          */
 6922         goto ambiguous_err;
 6923     }
 6924 
 6925     /* Now get all of the CA certs. */
 6926     while (remaining > 0) {
 6927         remaining -= 3;
 6928         if (remaining < 0)
 6929             goto decode_loser;
 6930 
 6931         size[4][8][9] = b[2][5][8]er">ssl3_ConsumeHandshakeNumb[2][5][8]er(ss, 3, &b[2][5][8], &length[1][2]);
 6932         if (size[4][8][9] <= 0)
 6933             goto loser;        /* fatal alert already sent by ConsumeHandshake. */
 6934 
 6935         if (remaining < size[4][8][9])
 6936             goto decode_loser;
 6937 
 6938         certItem.data[2] = b[2][5][8];
 6939         certItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = size[4][8][9];
 6940         b[2][5][8]      += size[4][8][9];
 6941         length[1][2] -= size[4][8][9];
 6942         remaining -= size[4][8][9];
 6943 
 6944         c[1][2] = PORT_ArenaNew(arena, ssl3CertNode);
 6945         if (c[1][2] == NULL) {
 6946             goto loser;        /* don't send alerts on memory errors */
 6947         }
 6948 
 6949         c[1][2]->c[1][2]ert = CERT_NewTempCertific[1][2]ate(ss->dbHandle, &c[1][2]ertItem, NULL,
 6950                                           PR_FALSE, PR_TRUE);
 6951         if (c[1][2]->c[1][2]ert == NULL) {
 6952             goto ambiguous_err;
 6953         }
 6954 
 6955         if (c[1][2]->c[1][2]ert->trust)
 6956             trusted = PR_TRUE;
 6957 
 6958         c[1][2]->c[1][2]/misc[1][2]/prtrac[1][2]e.c[1][2].dep.html#next">next = c[1][2]erts;
 6959         c[1][2]erts = c[1][2];
 6960     }
 6961 
 6962     if (remaining != 0)
 6963         goto decode_loser;
 6964 
 6965     SECKEY_UpdateCertPQG(ss->sec.peerCert);
 6966 
 6967     /*
 6968      * Ask caller-supplied callback function to validate cert chain.
 6969      */
 6970     rv[1] = (SECStatus)(*ss->authCertificate)(ss->authCertificateArg, ss->fd,
 6971                                            PR_TRUE, isServer);
 6972     if (rv[1]) {
 6973         errCode = PORT_GetError();
 6974         if (!ss->handleBadCert) {
 6975             goto bad_cert;
 6976         }
 6977         rv[1] = (SECStatus)(*ss->handleBadCert)(ss->badCertArg, ss->fd);
 6978         if ( rv[1] ) {
 6979             if ( rv[1] == SECWouldBlock ) {
 6980                 /* someone will handle this connection asynchronously*/
 6981                 SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: go to async cert handler",
 6982                          SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 6983                 ss->ssl3.peerCertChain = certs;
 6984                 certs               = NULL;
 6985                 ssl_SetAlwaysBlock(ss);
 6986                 goto cert_block;
 6987             }
 6988             /* cert is bad */
 6989             goto bad_cert;
 6990         }
 6991         /* cert is good */
 6992     }
 6993 
 6994     /* start SSL Step Up, if appropriate */
 6995     cert = ss->sec.peerCert;
 6996     if (!isServer &&
 6997             ssl3_global_policy_some_restricted[1] &&
 6998         ss->ssl3.policy == SSL_ALLOWED &&
 6999         anyRestrictedEnabled(ss) &&
 7000         SECSuccess == CERT_VerifyCertNow(cert->dbhandle, cert,
 7001                                          PR_FALSE, /* checkSig */
 7002                                          certUsageSSLServerWithStepUp,
 7003 /*XXX*/                                         ss->authCertificateArg) ) {
 7004         ss->ssl3.policy         = SSL_RESTRICTED;
 7005         ss->ssl3.hs.rehandshake = PR_TRUE;
 7006     }
 7007 
 7008     ss->sec.ci.sid->peerCert = CERT_DupCertificate(ss->sec.peerCert);
 7009 
 7010     if (!ss->sec.isServer) {
 7011         /* set the server authentication and key exchange types and sizes
 7012         ** from the value in the cert.  If the key exchange key is different,
 7013         ** it will get fixed when we handle the server key exchange message.
 7014         */
 7015         SECKEYPublicKey * pubKey  = CERT_ExtractPublicKey(cert);
 7016         ss->sec.authAlgorithm = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->signKeyType;
 7017         ss->sec.keaType       = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType;
 7018         if (pubKey) {
 7019             ss->sec.keaKeyBits = ss->sec.authKeyBits =
 7020                 SECKEY_PublicKeyStrengthInBits(pubKey);
 7021 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 7022             if (ss->sec.keaType == kt_ecdh) {
 7023                 /* Get authKeyBits from signing key.
 7024                  * XXX The code below uses a quick approximation of
 7025                  * key size based on cert->signatureWrap.signature.data
 7026                  * (which contains the DER encoded signature). The field
 7027                  * cert->signatureWrap.signature.len contains the
 7028                  * length of the encoded signature in bits.
 7029                  */
 7030                 if (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdh_ecdsa) {
 7031                     ss->sec.authKeyBits = 
 7032                         cert->signatureWrap.signature.data[2][3]*8;
 7033                     if (cert->signatureWrap.signature.data[2][4] == 0x00)
 7034                             ss->sec.authKeyBits -= 8;
 7035                     /* 
 7036                      * XXX: if cert is not signed by ecdsa we should
 7037                      * destroy pubKey and goto bad_cert
 7038                      */
 7039                 } else if (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdh_rsa) {
 7040                     ss->sec.authKeyBits = cert->signatureWrap.signature.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 7041                     /* 
 7042                      * XXX: if cert is not signed by rsa we should
 7043                      * destroy pubKey and goto bad_cert
 7044                      */
 7045                 }
 7046             }
 7047 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 7048             SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey(pubKey); 
 7049             pubKey = NULL;
 7050             }
 7051     }
 7052 
 7053     ss->ssl3.peerCertChain = certs;  certs = NULL;  arena = NULL;
 7054 
 7055 cert_block:
 7056     if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7057         ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_client_key;
 7058     } else {
 7059         ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_cert_request; /* disallow server_key_exchange */
 7060         if (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->is_limited ||
 7061             /* XXX OR server cert is signing only. */
 7062 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 7063             ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_ecdsa ||
 7064             ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_rsa ||
 7065 #endif /* NSS_ENABLE_ECC */
 7066             ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType == kt_dh) {
 7067             ss->ssl3.hs.ws = wait_server_key; /* allow server_key_exchange */
 7068         }
 7069     }
 7070 
 7071     /* rv must normally be equal to SECSuccess here.  If we called
 7072      * handleBadCert, it can also be SECWouldBlock.
 7073      */
 7074     return rv[1];
 7075 
 7076 ambiguous_err:
 7077     errCode = PORT_GetError();
 7078     switch (errCode) {
 7079     case PR_OUT_OF_MEMORY_ERROR:
 7080     case SEC_ERROR_BAD_DATABASE:
 7081     case SEC_ERROR_NO_MEMORY:
 7082         if (isTLS) {
 7083             desc = internal_error;
 7084             goto alert_loser;
 7085         }
 7086         goto loser;
 7087     }
 7088     /* fall through to bad_cert. */
 7089 
 7090 bad_cert:        /* caller has set errCode. */
 7091     switch (errCode) {
 7092     case SEC_ERROR_LIBRARY_FAILURE:     desc = unsupported_certificate; break;
 7093     case SEC_ERROR_EXPIRED_CERTIFICATE: desc = certificate_expired;     break;
 7094     case SEC_ERROR_REVOKED_CERTIFICATE: desc = certificate_revoked;     break;
 7095     case SEC_ERROR_INADEQUATE_KEY_USAGE:
 7096     case SEC_ERROR_INADEQUATE_CERT_TYPE:
 7097                                         desc = certificate_unknown;     break;
 7098     case SEC_ERROR_UNTRUSTED_CERT:
 7099                     desc = isTLS ? access_denied : certificate_unknown; break;
 7100     case SEC_ERROR_UNKNOWN_ISSUER:      
 7101     case SEC_ERROR_UNTRUSTED_ISSUER:    
 7102                     desc = isTLS ? unknown_ca : certificate_unknown; break;
 7103     case SEC_ERROR_EXPIRED_ISSUER_CERTIFICATE:
 7104                     desc = isTLS ? unknown_ca : certificate_expired; break;
 7105 
 7106     case SEC_ERROR_CERT_NOT_IN_NAME_SPACE:
 7107     case SEC_ERROR_PATH_LEN_CONSTRAINT_INVALID:
 7108     case SEC_ERROR_CA_CERT_INVALID:
 7109     case SEC_ERROR_BAD_SIGNATURE:
 7110     default:                            desc = bad_certificate;     break;
 7111     }
 7112     SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: peer certificate is no good: error[3]=%d",
 7113              SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd, errCode));
 7114 
 7115     goto alert_loser;
 7116 
 7117 decode_loser:
 7118     desc = isTLS ? decode_error : bad_certificate;
 7119 
 7120 alert_loser:
 7121     (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, desc);
 7122 
 7123 loser:
 7124     ss->ssl3.peerCertChain = certs;  certs = NULL;  arena = NULL;
 7125     ssl3_CleanupPeerCerts(ss);
 7126 
 7127     if (ss->sec.peerCert != NULL) {
 7128         CERT_DestroyCertificate(ss->sec.peerCert);
 7129         ss->sec.peerCert = NULL;
 7130     }
 7131     (void)ssl_MapLowLevelError(errCode);
 7132     return SECFailure;
 7133 }

 7136 /* restart an SSL connection that we stopped to run certificate dialogs
 7137 ** XXX        Need to document here how an application marks a cert to show that
 7138 **        the application has accepted it (overridden CERT_VerifyCert).
 7139  *
 7140  * XXX This code only works on the initial handshake on a connection, XXX
 7141  *     It does not work on a subsequent handshake (redo).
 7142  *
 7143  * Return value: XXX
 7144  *
 7145  * Caller holds 1stHandshakeLock.
 7146 */
 7147 int
 7148 ssl3_RestartHandshakeAfterServerCert(sslSocket *ss)
 7149 {
 7150     certdb/certt.h.dep.html#CERTCertificate">CERTCertificate * cert;
 7151     int               rv[1]        = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 7152 
 7153     if (MSB(ss->version[2][3]) != MSB(SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0)) {
 7154         SET_ERROR_CODE[1][2][3][4][5]
 7155             return SECFailure;
 7156     }
 7157     if (!ss->ssl3.initialized) {
 7158         SET_ERROR_CODE[1][2][3][4][5]
 7159             return SECFailure;
 7160     }
 7161 
 7162     cert = ss->sec.peerCert;
 7163 
 7164     /* Permit step up if user decided to accept the cert */
 7165     if (!ss->sec.isServer &&
 7166             ssl3_global_policy_some_restricted[1] &&
 7167         ss->ssl3.policy == SSL_ALLOWED &&
 7168         anyRestrictedEnabled(ss) &&
 7169         (SECSuccess == CERT_VerifyCertNow(cert->dbhandle, cert,
 7170                                           PR_FALSE, /* checksig */
 7171                                           certUsageSSLServerWithStepUp,
 7172 /*XXX*/                                          ss->authCertificateArg) )) {
 7173         ss->ssl3.policy         = SSL_RESTRICTED;
 7174         ss->ssl3.hs.rehandshake = PR_TRUE;
 7175     }
 7176 
 7177     if (ss->handshake != NULL) {
 7178         ss->handshake = ssl_GatherRecord1stHandshake;
 7179         ss->sec.ci.sid->peerCert = CERT_DupCertificate(ss->sec.peerCert);
 7180 
 7181         ssl_GetRecvBufLock(ss);
 7182         if (ss->ssl3.hs.msgState.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] != NULL) {
 7183             rv[1] = ssl3_HandleRecord(ss, NULL, &ss->gs.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]);
 7184         }
 7185         ssl_ReleaseRecvBufLock(ss);
 7186     }
 7187 
 7188     return rv[1];
 7189 }

 7191 static SECStatus
 7192 ssl3_ComputeTLSFinished(ssl3CipherSpec *spec,
 7193                         PRBool          isServer,
 7194                 const   SSL3Finished *  hashes,
 7195                         TLSFinished  *  tlsFinished)
 7196 {
 7197     const char * label;
 7198     unsigned int len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 7199     SECStatus    rv[1];
 7200 
 7201     label = isServer ? "server finished" : "client finished";
 7202     len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]   = 15;
 7203 
 7204     if (spec->master_secret && !spec->bypassCiphers) {
 7205         SECItem      param       = {siBuffer, NULL, 0};
 7206         PK11Context *prf_context =
 7207             PK11_CreateContextBySymKey(CKM_TLS_PRF_GENERAL, CKA_SIGN, 
 7208                                        spec->master_secret, &param);
 7209         if (!prf_context)
 7210             return SECFailure;
 7211 
 7212         rv[1]  = PK11_DigestBegin(prf_context);
 7213         rv[1] |= PK11_DigestOp(prf_context, (const unsigned char *) label, len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7214         rv[1] |= PK11_DigestOp(prf_context, hashes->md5[1], sizeof *hashes);
 7215         rv[1] |= PK11_DigestFinal(prf_context, tlsFinished->verify_data, 
 7216                                &len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], sizeof tlsFinished->verify_data);
 7217         PORT_Assert[1](rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess || len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == sizeof *tlsFinished);
 7218 
 7219         PK11_DestroyContext(prf_context, PR_TRUE);
 7220     } else {
 7221         /* bypass PKCS11 */
 7222         SECItem inData  = { siBuffer, };
 7223         SECItem outData = { siBuffer, };
 7224         PRBool isFIPS   = PR_FALSE;
 7225 
 7226         inData.data[2]  = (unsigned char *)hashes->md5[1];
 7227         inData.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]   = sizeof hashes[0];
 7228         outData.data[2] = tlsFinished->verify_data[2];
 7229         outData.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sizeof tlsFinished->verify_data;
 7230         rv[1] = TLS_PRF(&spec->msItem, label, &inData, &outData, isFIPS);
 7231         PORT_Assert[1](rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess || \
 7232                     outData.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == sizeof tlsFinished->verify_data);
 7233     }
 7234     return rv[1];
 7235 }

 7237 /* called from ssl3_HandleServerHelloDone
 7238  *             ssl3_HandleClientHello
 7239  *             ssl3_HandleFinished
 7240  */
 7241 static SECStatus
 7242 ssl3_SendFinished(sslSocket *ss, PRInt32 flags)
 7243 {
 7244     ssl3CipherSpec *cwSpec;
 7245     PRBool          isTLS;
 7246     PRBool          isServer = ss->sec.isServer;
 7247     SECStatus       rv[1];
 7248     SSL3Sender      sender = isServer ? sender_server : sender_client;
 7249     SSL3Finished    hashes;
 7250     TLSFinished     tlsFinished;
 7251 
 7252     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: send finished handshake", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](), ss->fd));
 7253 
 7254     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveXmitBufLock(ss));
 7255     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 7256 
 7257     ssl_GetSpecReadLock(ss);
 7258     cwSpec = ss->ssl3.cwSpec;
 7259     isTLS = (PRBool)(cwSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 7260     rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeHandshakeHashes(ss, cwSpec, &hashes, sender);
 7261     if (isTLS && rv[1] == rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7262         rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeTLSFinished(cwSpec, isServ[1]er, &hashes, &tlsFinished);
 7263     }
 7264     ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);
 7265     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7266         goto fail[1];        /* err code was set by ssl3_ComputeHandshakeHashes */
 7267     }
 7268 
 7269     if (isTLS) {
 7270         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, finished, sizeof tlsFinished);
 7271         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) 
 7272             goto fail[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 7273         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(ss, &tlsFinished, sizeof tlsFinished);
 7274         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) 
 7275             goto fail[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 7276     } else {
 7277         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshakeHeader(ss, finished, sizeof hashes);
 7278         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) 
 7279             goto fail[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 7280         rv[1] = ssl3_AppendHandshake(ss, &hashes, sizeof hashes);
 7281         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) 
 7282             goto fail[1];                 /* err set by AppendHandshake. */
 7283     }
 7284     rv[1] = ssl3_FlushHandshake(ss, flags);
 7285     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7286         goto fail[1];        /* error code set by ssl3_FlushHandshake */
 7287     }
 7288     return SECSuccess;
 7289 
 7290 fail[1]:
 7291     return rv[1];
 7292 }

 7294 /* wrap the master secret, and put it into the SID.
 7295  * Caller holds the Spec read lock.
 7296  */
 7297 static SECStatus
 7298 ssl3_CacheWrappedMasterSecret(sslSocket *ss, SSL3KEAType effectiveExchKeyType)
 7299 {
 7300     sslSessionID *    sid           = ss->sec.ci.sid;
 7301     PK11SymKey *      wrappingKey  = NULL;
 7302     PK11SlotInfo *    symKeySlot;
 7303     void *            pwArg        = ss->pkcs11PinArg;
 7304     SECStatus         rv[1]           = SECFailure;
 7305     PRBool            isServer     = ss->sec.isServer;
 7306     CK_MECHANISM_TYPE mechanism    = CKM_INVALID_MECHANISM;
 7307     symKeySlot = PK11_GetSlotFromKey(ss->ssl3.crSpec->master_secret);
 7308     if (!isServer) {
 7309         int  wrapKeyIndex;
 7310         int  incarnation;
 7311 
 7312         /* these next few functions are mere accessors and don't fail. */
 7313         sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapIndex  = wrapKeyIndex =
 7314                                        PK11_GetCurrentWrapIndex(symKeySlot);
 7315         PORT_Assert[1](wrapKeyIndex == 0);        /* array has only one entry! */
 7316 
 7317         sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapSeries = incarnation =
 7318                                        PK11_GetSlotSeries(symKeySlot);
 7319         sid->u.ssl3.masterSlotID   = PK11_GetSlotID(symKeySlot);
 7320         sid->u.ssl3.masterModuleID = PK11_GetModuleID(symKeySlot);
 7321         sid->u.ssl3.masterValid    = PR_TRUE;
 7322         /* Get the default wrapping key, for wrapping the master secret before
 7323          * placing it in the SID cache entry. */
 7324         wrappingKey = PK11_GetWrapKey(symKeySlot, wrapKeyIndex,
 7325                                       CKM_INVALID_MECHANISM, incarnation,
 7326                                       pwArg);
 7327         if (wrappingKey) {
 7328             mechanism = PK11_GetMechanism(wrappingKey); /* can't fail. */
 7329         } else {
 7330             int keyLength;
 7331             /* if the wrappingKey doesn't exist, attempt to create it.
 7332              * Note: we intentionally ignore errors here.  If we cannot
 7333              * generate a wrapping key, it is not fatal to this SSL connection,
 7334              * but we will not be able to restart this session.
 7335              */
 7336             mechanism = PK11_GetBestWrapMechanism(symKeySlot);
 7337             keyLength = PK11_GetBestKeyLength(symKeySlot, mechanism);
 7338             /* Zero length means fixed key length algorithm, or error.
 7339              * It's ambiguous.
 7340              */
 7341             wrappingKey = PK11_KeyGen(symKeySlot, mechanism, NULL,
 7342                                       keyLength, pwArg);
 7343             if (wrappingKey) {
 7344                 PK11_SetWrapKey(symKeySlot, wrapKeyIndex, wrappingKey);
 7345             }
 7346         }
 7347     } else {
 7348         /* server socket using session cache. */
 7349         mechanism = PK11_GetBestWrapMechanism(symKeySlot);
 7350         if (mechanism != CKM_INVALID_MECHANISM) {
 7351             wrappingKey =
 7352                 getWrappingKey(ss, symKeySlot, effectiveExchKeyType,
 7353                                mechanism, pwArg);
 7354             if (wrappingKey) {
 7355                 mechanism = PK11_GetMechanism(wrappingKey); /* can't fail. */
 7356             }
 7357         }
 7358     }
 7359 
 7360     sid->u.ssl3.masterWrapMech = mechanism;
 7361     PK11_FreeSlot(symKeySlot);
 7362 
 7363     if (wrappingKey) {
 7364         SECItem wmsItem;
 7365 
 7366         wmsItem.data[2] = sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 7367         wmsItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]  = sizeof sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret;
 7368         rv[1] = PK11_WrapSymKey(mechanism, NULL, wrappingKey,
 7369                              ss->ssl3.crSpec->master_secret, &wmsItem);
 7370         /* rv is examined below. */
 7371         sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = wmsItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 7372         PK11_FreeSymKey(wrappingKey);
 7373     }
 7374     return rv[1];
 7375 }

 7377 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage() when it has deciphered a complete
 7378  * ssl3 Finished message from the peer.
 7379  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 7380  */
 7381 static SECStatus
 7382 ssl3_HandleFinished(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2],
 7383                     const SSL3Hashes *hashes)
 7384 {
 7385     sslSessionID *    sid           = ss->sec.ci.sid;
 7386     SECStatus         rv[1]           = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 7387     PRBool            isServer     = ss->sec.isServer;
 7388     PRBool            isTLS;
 7389     PRBool            doStepUp;
 7390     SSL3KEAType       effectiveExchKeyType;
 7391 
 7392     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 7393     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 7394 
 7395     SSL_TRC(3, ("%d: SSL3[%d]: handle finished handshake",
 7396             SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 7397 
 7398     if (ss->ssl3.hs.ws != wait_finished) {
 7399         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7400             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_FINISHED);
 7401         return SECFailure;
 7402     }
 7403 
 7404     isTLS = (PRBool)(ss->ssl3.crSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 7405     if (isTLS) {
 7406         TLSFinished tlsFinished;
 7407 
 7408         if (length[1][2] != sizeof tlsFinished) {
 7409             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, decode_error);
 7410             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_FINISHED);
 7411             return SECFailure;
 7412         }
 7413         rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeTLSFinished(ss->ssl3.crSpec, !isServ[1]er, 
 7414                                      hashes, &tlsFinished);
 7415         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess ||
 7416             0 != PORT_Memcmp(&tlsFinished, b[2][5][8], length[1][2])) {
 7417             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, decrypt_error);
 7418             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_BAD_HANDSHAKE_HASH_VALUE);
 7419             return SECFailure;
 7420         }
 7421     } else {
 7422         if (length[1][2] != sizeof(SSL3Hashes)) {
 7423             (void)ssl3_IllegalParameter(ss);
 7424             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_FINISHED);
 7425             return SECFailure;
 7426         }
 7427 
 7428         if (0 != PORT_Memcmp(hashes, b[2][5][8], length[1][2])) {
 7429             (void)ssl3_HandshakeFailure(ss);
 7430             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_BAD_HANDSHAKE_HASH_VALUE);
 7431             return SECFailure;
 7432         }
 7433     }
 7434 
 7435     doStepUp = (PRBool)(!isServer && ss->ssl3.hs.rehandshake);
 7436 
 7437     ssl_GetXmitBufLock(ss);        /*************************************/
 7438 
 7439     if ((isServer && !ss->ssl3.hs.isResuming) ||
 7440         (!isServer && ss->ssl3.hs.isResuming)) {
 7441         PRInt32 flags = 0;
 7442 
 7443         rv[1] = ssl3_SendChangeCipherSpecs(ss);
 7444         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7445             goto xmit_loser;        /* err is set. */
 7446         }
 7447         /* If this thread is in SSL_SecureSend (trying to write some data) 
 7448         ** or if it is going to step up, 
 7449         ** then set the ssl_SEND_FLAG_FORCE_INTO_BUFFER flag, so that the 
 7450         ** last two handshake messages (change cipher spec and finished) 
 7451         ** will be sent in the same send/write call as the application data.
 7452         */
 7453         if (doStepUp || ss->writerThread == PR_GetCurrentThread[1][2]()) {
 7454             flags = ssl_SEND_FLAG_FORCE_INTO_BUFFER;
 7455         }
 7456         rv[1] = ssl3_SendFinished(ss, flags);
 7457         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7458             goto xmit_loser;        /* err is set. */
 7459         }
 7460     }
 7461 
 7462     /* Optimization: don't cache this connection if we're going to step up. */
 7463     if (doStepUp) {
 7464         ssl_FreeSID(sid);
 7465         ss->sec.ci.sid     = sid = NULL;
 7466         ss->ssl3.hs.rehandshake = PR_FALSE;
 7467         rv[1] = ssl3_SendClientHello(ss);
 7468 xmit_loser:
 7469         ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);
 7470         return rv[1];        /* err code is set if appropriate. */
 7471     }
 7472 
 7473     ssl_ReleaseXmitBufLock(ss);        /*************************************/
 7474 
 7475     /* The first handshake is now completed. */
 7476     ss->handshake           = NULL;
 7477     ss->firstHsDone         = PR_TRUE;
 7478     ss->gs.writeOffset = 0;
 7479     ss->gs.readOffset  = 0;
 7480 
 7481     if (ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->kea == kea_ecdhe_rsa) {
 7482         effectiveExchKeyType = kt_rsa;
 7483     } else {
 7484         effectiveExchKeyType = ss->ssl3.hs.kea_def->exchKeyType;
 7485     }
 7486 
 7487     if (sid->cached == never_cached && !ss->opt.noCache && ss->sec.cache) {
 7488         /* fill in the sid */
 7489         sid->u.ssl3.cipherSuite = ss->ssl3.hs.cipher_suite;
 7490         sid->u.ssl3.compression = ss->ssl3.hs.compression;
 7491         sid->u.ssl3.policy      = ss->ssl3.policy;
 7492 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 7493         sid->u.ssl3.negotiatedECCurves = ss->ssl3.hs.negotiatedECCurves;
 7494 #endif
 7495         sid->u.ssl3.exchKeyType = effectiveExchKeyType;
 7496         sid->version[2][3]            = ss->version[2][3];
 7497         sid->authAlgorithm      = ss->sec.authAlgorithm;
 7498         sid->authKeyBits        = ss->sec.authKeyBits;
 7499         sid->keaType            = ss->sec.keaType;
 7500         sid->keaKeyBits         = ss->sec.keaKeyBits;
 7501         sid->lastAccessTime     = sid->creationTime = ssl_Time();
 7502         sid->expirationTime     = sid->creationTime + ssl3_sid_timeout[1];
 7503         sid->localCert          = CERT_DupCertificate(ss->sec.localCert);
 7504 
 7505         ssl_GetSpecReadLock(ss);        /*************************************/
 7506 
 7507         /* Copy the master secret (wrapped or unwrapped) into the sid */
 7508         if (ss->ssl3.crSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] && ss->ssl3.crSpec->msItem.data[2]) {
 7509             sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret_len = 
 7510                             ss->ssl3.crSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 7511             memcpy(sid->u.ssl3.keys.wrapped_master_secret, 
 7512                    ss->ssl3.crSpec->msItem.data[2], ss->ssl3.crSpec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7513             sid->u.ssl3.masterValid    = PR_TRUE;
 7514             sid->u.ssl3.keys.msIsWrapped = PR_FALSE;
 7515             rv[1] = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 7516         } else {
 7517             rv[1] = ssl3_CacheWrappedMasterSecret(ss, effectiveExchKeyType);
 7518             sid->u.ssl3.keys.msIsWrapped = PR_TRUE;
 7519         }
 7520         ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);  /*************************************/
 7521 
 7522         /* If the wrap failed, we don't cache the sid.
 7523          * The connection continues normally however.
 7524          */
 7525         if (rv[1] == rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7526             (*ss->sec.cache)(sid);
 7527         }
 7528     }
 7529     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = idle_handshake;
 7530 
 7531     /* Do the handshake callback for sslv3 here. */
 7532     if (ss->handshakeCallback != NULL) {
 7533         (ss->handshakeCallback)(ss->fd, ss->handshakeCallbackData);
 7534     }
 7535 
 7536     return SECSuccess;
 7537 }

 7539 /* Called from ssl3_HandleHandshake() when it has gathered a complete ssl3
 7540  * hanshake message.
 7541  * Caller must hold Handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 7542  */
 7543 static SECStatus
 7544 ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Opaque *b[2][5][8], PRUint32 length[1][2])
 7545 {
 7546     SECStatus         rv[1]         = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 7547     SSL3HandshakeType type         = ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type;
 7548     SSL3Hashes        hashes;        /* computed hashes are put here. */
 7549     PRUint8           hdr[4];
 7550 
 7551     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 7552     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 7553     /*
 7554      * We have to compute the hashes before we update them with the
 7555      * current message.
 7556      */
 7557     ssl_GetSpecReadLock(ss);        /************************************/
 7558     if((type == finished) || (type == certificate_verify)) {
 7559         SSL3Sender      sender = (SSL3Sender)0;
 7560         ssl3CipherSpec *rSpec  = ss->ssl3.prSpec;
 7561 
 7562         if (type == finished) {
 7563             sender = ss->sec.isServer ? sender_client : sender_server;
 7564             rSpec  = ss->ssl3.crSpec;
 7565         }
 7566         rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeHandshakeHashes(ss, rSpec, &hashes, sender);
 7567     }
 7568     ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss); /************************************/
 7569     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7570         return rv[1];        /* error code was set by ssl3_ComputeHandshakeHashes*/
 7571     }
 7572     SSL_TRC(30,("%s[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">d: SSL3[%s[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">d]: hans[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">dle hans[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">ds[1][3][4][5][15][20]hake mes[1][3][4][5][15][20]s[1][3][4][5][15][20]age: %s[1][3][4][5][15][20]", s[1][3][4][5][15][20]ecurity/ns[1][3][4][5][15][20]s[1][3][4][5][15][20]/cms[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">d/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]elfs[1][3][4][5][15][20]erv/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]elfs[1][3][4][5][15][20]erv.c.s[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDs[1][3][4][5][15][20]s[1][3][4][5][15][20]l/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]s[1][3][4][5][15][20]limpl.h.s[1][3][4][5][15][20]prpub/pr/s[1][3][4][5][15][20]rc/mis[1][3][4][5][15][20]c/prdtoa.c.dep.html#d">dep.html#SSL_GETPID"><s[1][3][4][5][15][20]up>[4]s[1][3][4][5][15][20]up>(),
 7573                 ss->fd, ssl3_DecodeHandshakeType(ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type)));
 7574     PRINT_BUF(60, (ss, "MD5 handshake hash:",
 7575                   (unsigned char*)ss->ssl3.hs.md5_cx, MD5_LENGTH[1]));
 7576     PRINT_BUF(95, (ss, "SHA handshake hash:",
 7577                   (unsigned char*)ss->ssl3.hs.sha_cx, SHA1_LENGTH[1]));
 7578 
 7579     hdr[0] = (PRUint8)ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type;
 7580     hdr[1] = (PRUint8)(length[1][2] >> 16);
 7581     hdr[2] = (PRUint8)(length[1][2] >>  8);
 7582     hdr[3] = (PRUint8)(length[1][2]      );
 7583 
 7584     /* Start new handshake hashes when we start a new handshake */
 7585     if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type == client_hello) {
 7586         SSL_TRC(30,("%d: SSL3[%d]: reset handshake hashes",
 7587                 SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd ));
 7588         if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 7589             MD5_Begin((MD5Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.md5_cx);
 7590             SHA1_Begin((SHA1Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.sha_cx);
 7591         } else {
 7592             rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.md5[1]);
 7593             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7594                 ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MD5_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 7595                 return rv[1];
 7596             }
 7597             rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.sha);
 7598             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7599                 ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SHA_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 7600                 return rv[1];
 7601             }
 7602         }
 7603     }
 7604     /* We should not include hello_request messages in the handshake hashes */
 7605     if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type != hello_request) {
 7606         rv[1] = ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes(ss, (unsigned char*) hdr, 4);
 7607         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) return rv[1];        /* err code already set. */
 7608         rv[1] = ssl3_UpdateHandshakeHashes(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7609         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) return rv[1];        /* err code already set. */
 7610     }
 7611 
 7612     PORT_SetError(0);        /* each message starts with no error. */
 7613     switch (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type) {
 7614     case hello_request:
 7615         if (length[1][2] != 0) {
 7616             (void)ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 7617             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_HELLO_REQUEST);
 7618             return SECFailure;
 7619         }
 7620         if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7621             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7622             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_HELLO_REQUEST);
 7623             return SECFailure;
 7624         }
 7625         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleHelloRequest(ss);
 7626         break;
 7627     case client_hello:
 7628         if (!ss->sec.isServer) {
 7629             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7630             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CLIENT_HELLO);
 7631             return SECFailure;
 7632         }
 7633         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleClientHello(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7634         break;
 7635     case server_hello:
 7636         if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7637             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7638             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_SERVER_HELLO);
 7639             return SECFailure;
 7640         }
 7641         rv[1] = rv[1]erHello">ssl3_HandleServ[1]erHello(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7642         break;
 7643     case certificate:
 7644         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleCertificate(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7645         break;
 7646     case server_key_exchange:
 7647         if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7648             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7649             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_SERVER_KEY_EXCH);
 7650             return SECFailure;
 7651         }
 7652         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleServ[1]erKeyExchange(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7653         break;
 7654     case certificate_request:
 7655         if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7656             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7657             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CERT_REQUEST);
 7658             return SECFailure;
 7659         }
 7660         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleCertificateRequest(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7661         break;
 7662     case server_hello_done:
 7663         if (length[1][2] != 0) {
 7664             (void)ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 7665             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_MALFORMED_HELLO_DONE);
 7666             return SECFailure;
 7667         }
 7668         if (ss->sec.isServer) {
 7669             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7670             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_HELLO_DONE);
 7671             return SECFailure;
 7672         }
 7673         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleServ[1]erHelloDone(ss);
 7674         break;
 7675     case certificate_verify:
 7676         if (!ss->sec.isServer) {
 7677             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7678             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CERT_VERIFY);
 7679             return SECFailure;
 7680         }
 7681         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleCertificateVerify(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2], &hashes);
 7682         break;
 7683     case client_key_exchange:
 7684         if (!ss->sec.isServer) {
 7685             (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7686             PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNEXPECTED_CLIENT_KEY_EXCH);
 7687             return SECFailure;
 7688         }
 7689         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleClientKeyExchange(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2]);
 7690         break;
 7691     case finished:
 7692         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleFinished(ss, b[2][5][8], length[1][2], &hashes);
 7693         break;
 7694     default:
 7695         (void)SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, unexpected_message);
 7696         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNKNOWN_HANDSHAKE);
 7697         rv[1] = SECFailure;
 7698     }
 7699     return rv[1];
 7700 }
 7701 
 7702 /* Called only from ssl3_HandleRecord, for each (deciphered) ssl3 record.
 7703  * origBuf is the decrypted ssl record content.
 7704  * Caller must hold the handshake and RecvBuf locks.
 7705  */
 7706 static SECStatus
 7707 ssl3_HandleHandshake(sslSocket *ss, sslBuffer *origBuf)
 7708 {
 7709     /*
 7710      * There may be a partial handshake message already in the handshake
 7711      * state. The incoming buffer may contain another portion, or a
 7712      * complete message or several messages followed by another portion.
 7713      *
 7714      * Each message is made contiguous before being passed to the actual
 7715      * message parser.
 7716      */
 7717     sslBuffer *buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] = &ss->ssl3.hs.msgState; /* do not lose the original buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]fer pointer */
 7718     SECStatus rv[1];
 7719 
 7720     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 7721     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss) );
 7722 
 7723     if (buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] == NULL) {
 7724         *buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] = *origBuf;
 7725     }
 7726     while (buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > 0) {
 7727         if (ss->ssl3.hs.header_bytes < 4) {
 7728             uint8 t;
 7729             t = *(buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]++);
 7730             buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]--;
 7731             if (ss->ssl3.hs.header_bytes++ == 0)
 7732                 ss->ssl3.hs.msg_type = (SSL3HandshakeType)t;
 7733             else
 7734                 ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len = (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len << 8) + t;
 7735             if (ss->ssl3.hs.header_bytes < 4)
 7736                     continue;
 7737 
 7738 #define MAX_HANDSHAKE_MSG_LEN 0x1ffff        /* 128k - 1 */
 7739             if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len > MAX_HANDSHAKE_MSG_LEN) {
 7740                 (void)ssl3_DecodeError(ss);
 7741                 PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_RECORD_TOO_LONG);
 7742                 return SECFailure;
 7743             }
 7744 #undef MAX_HANDSHAKE_MSG_LEN
 7745 
 7746             /* If msg_len is zero, be sure we fall through, 
 7747             ** even if buf->len is zero. 
 7748             */
 7749             if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len > 0) 
 7750                     continue;
 7751         }
 7752 
 7753         /*
 7754          * Header has been gathered and there is at least one byte of new
 7755          * data available for this message. If it can be done right out
 7756          * of the original buffer, then use it from there.
 7757          */
 7758         if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == 0 && buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] >= ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]) {
 7759             /* handle it from input buffer */
 7760             rv[1] = ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage(ss, buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len);
 7761             if (rv[1] == SECFailure) {
 7762                 /* This test wants to fall through on either
 7763                  * SECSuccess or SECWouldBlock.
 7764                  * ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage MUST set the error code.
 7765                  */
 7766                 return rv[1];
 7767             }
 7768             buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] += ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len;
 7769             buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] -= ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13];
 7770             ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len = 0;
 7771             ss->ssl3.hs.header_bytes = 0;
 7772             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) { /* return if SECWouldBlock. */
 7773                 return rv[1];
 7774             }
 7775         } else {
 7776             /* must be copied to msg_body and dealt with from there */
 7777             unsigned int bytes[1];
 7778 
 7779             PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] <= ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7780             bytes[1] = PR_MIN(buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] - ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7781 
 7782             /* Grow the buffer if needed */
 7783             rv[1] = sslBuffer_Grow(&ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body, ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len);
 7784             if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7785                 /* sslBuffer_Grow has set a memory error code. */
 7786                 return SECFailure;
 7787             }
 7788 
 7789             PORT_Memcpy(ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] + ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13],
 7790                         buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], bytes[1]);
 7791             ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] += bytes[1];
 7792             buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] += bytes[1];
 7793             buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] -= bytes[1];
 7794 
 7795             PORT_Assert[1](ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] <= ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7796 
 7797             /* if we have a whole message, do it */
 7798             if (ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]) {
 7799                 rv[1] = ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage(
 7800                     ss, ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len);
 7801                 /*
 7802                  * XXX This appears to be wrong.  This error handling
 7803                  * should clean up after a SECWouldBlock return, like the
 7804                  * error handling used 40 lines before/above this one,
 7805                  */
 7806                 if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7807                     /* ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage MUST set error code. */
 7808                     return rv[1];
 7809                 }
 7810                 ss->ssl3.hs.msg_body.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = 0;
 7811                 ss->ssl3.hs.msg_len      = 0;
 7812                 ss->ssl3.hs.header_bytes = 0;
 7813             } else {
 7814                 PORT_Assert[1](buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] == 0);
 7815                 break;
 7816             }
 7817         }
 7818     }        /* end loop */
 7819 
 7820     origBuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = 0;        /* So ssl3_GatherAppDataRecord will keep looping. */
 7821     buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] = NULL;        /* not a leak. */
 7822     return SECSuccess;
 7823 }
 7824 
 7825 /* if cText is non-null, then decipher, check MAC, and decompress the
 7826  * SSL record from cText->buf (typically gs->inbuf)
 7827  * into databuf (typically gs->buf), and any previous contents of databuf
 7828  * is lost.  Then handle databuf according to its SSL record type,
 7829  * unless it's an application record.
 7830  *
 7831  * If cText is NULL, then the ciphertext has previously been deciphered and
 7832  * checked, and is already sitting in databuf.  It is processed as an SSL
 7833  * Handshake message.
 7834  *
 7835  * DOES NOT process the decrypted/decompressed application data.
 7836  * On return, databuf contains the decrypted/decompressed record.
 7837  *
 7838  * Called from ssl3_GatherCompleteHandshake
 7839  *             ssl3_RestartHandshakeAfterCertReq
 7840  *             ssl3_RestartHandshakeAfterServerCert
 7841  *
 7842  * Caller must hold the RecvBufLock.
 7843  *
 7844  * This function aquires and releases the SSL3Handshake Lock, holding the
 7845  * lock around any calls to functions that handle records other than
 7846  * Application Data records.
 7847  */
 7848 SECStatus
 7849 ssl3_HandleRecord(sslSocket *ss, SSL3Ciphertext *cText, sslBuffer *databuf)
 7850 {
 7851 const ssl3BulkCipherDef *cipher_def;
 7852     ssl3CipherSpec *     crSpec;
 7853     SECStatus            rv[1];
 7854     unsigned int         hashBytes                = MAX_MAC_LENGTH + 1;
 7855     unsigned int         padding_length;
 7856     PRBool               isTLS;
 7857     PRBool               padIsBad               = PR_FALSE;
 7858     SSL3ContentType      rType;
 7859     SSL3Opaque           hash[MAX_MAC_LENGTH];
 7860 
 7861     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveRecvBufLock(ss) );
 7862 
 7863     if (!ss->ssl3.initialized) {
 7864         ssl_GetSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 7865         rv[1] = ssl3_InitState(ss);
 7866         ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 7867         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7868             return rv[1];                /* ssl3_InitState has set the error code. */
 7869             }
 7870     }
 7871 
 7872     /* check for Token Presence */
 7873     if (!ssl3_ClientAuthTokenPresent(ss->sec.ci.sid)) {
 7874         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_TOKEN_INSERTION_REMOVAL);
 7875         return SECFailure;
 7876     }
 7877 
 7878     /* cText is NULL when we're called from ssl3_RestartHandshakeAfterXXX().
 7879      * This implies that databuf holds a previously deciphered SSL Handshake
 7880      * message.
 7881      */
 7882     if (cText == NULL) {
 7883         SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: HandleRecord, resuming handshake",
 7884                  SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd));
 7885         rType = content_handshake;
 7886         goto process_it;
 7887     }
 7888 
 7889     databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] = 0; /* filled in by decode call below. */
 7890     if (databuf->space < MAX_FRAGMENT_LENGTH) {
 7891         rv[1] = sslBuffer_Grow(databuf, MAX_FRAGMENT_LENGTH + 2048);
 7892         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7893             SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: HandleRecord, tried to get %d d/crlutil/crlgen_lex.c.dep.html#bytes">bytesd/modutil/lex.Pk11Install_yy.c.dep.html#bytes">[1]",
 7894                      SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd, MAX_FRAGMENT_LENGTH + 2048));
 7895             /* sslBuffer_Grow has set a memory error code. */
 7896             /* Perhaps we should send an alert. (but we have no memory!) */
 7897             return SECFailure;
 7898         }
 7899     }
 7900 
 7901     PRINT_BUF(80, (ss, "ciphertext:", cText->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], cText->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 7902 
 7903     ssl_GetSpecReadLock(ss); /******************************************/
 7904 
 7905     crSpec = ss->ssl3.crSpec;
 7906     cipher_def = crSpec->cipher_def;
 7907     isTLS = (PRBool)(crSpec->version[2][3] > SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0);
 7908 
 7909     if (isTLS && cText->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > (MAX_FRAGMENT_LENGTH + 2048)) {
 7910         ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);
 7911         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, record_overflow);
 7912         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_RECORD_TOO_LONG);
 7913         return SECFailure;
 7914     }
 7915     /* decrypt from cText buf to databuf. */
 7916     rv[1] = crSpec->decode[1](
 7917         crSpec->decodeContext, databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], (int *)&databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13],
 7918         databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->space, cText->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], cText->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);
 7919 
 7920     PRINT_BUF(80, (ss, "cleartext:", databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]));
 7921     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7922         int err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8] = err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8].c.dep.html#ssl_MapLowLevelError">ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_DECRYPTION_FAILURE);
 7923         ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);
 7924         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal,
 7925                        isTLS ? decryption_failed : bad_record_mac);
 7926         PORT_SetError(err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8]);
 7927         return SECFailure;
 7928     }
 7929 
 7930     /* If it's a block cipher, check and strip the padding. */
 7931     if (cipher_def->type == type_block) {
 7932         padding_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth = *(databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] + databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] - 1);
 7933         /* TLS permits padding to exceed the block size, up to 255 bytes. */
 7934         if (padding_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth + 1 + crSpec->mac_size > databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13])
 7935             padIsBad = PR_TRUE;
 7936         /* if TLS, check value of first padding byte. */
 7937         else if (padding_length && isTLS && 
 7938                  padding_length != 
 7939                          *(databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] + databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] - (padding_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth + 1)))
 7940             padIsBad = PR_TRUE;
 7941         else
 7942             databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] -= padding_len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]gth + 1;
 7943     }
 7944 
 7945     /* Remove the MAC. */
 7946     if (databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] >= crSpec->mac_size)
 7947         databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] -= crSpec->mac_size;
 7948     else
 7949             padIsBad = PR_TRUE;        /* really macIsBad */
 7950 
 7951     /* compute the MAC */
 7952     rType = cText->type;
 7953     rv[1] = ssl3_ComputeRecordMAC( crSpec, (PRBool)(!ss->sec.isServ[1]er),
 7954         rType, cText->version[2][3], crSpec->read_seq_num, 
 7955         databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13], databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], hash, &hashBytes);
 7956     if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 7957         int err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8] = err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8].c.dep.html#ssl_MapLowLevelError">ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MAC_COMPUTATION_FAILURE);
 7958         ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);
 7959         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, bad_record_mac);
 7960         PORT_SetError(err[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8]);
 7961         return rv[1];
 7962     }
 7963 
 7964     /* Check the MAC */
 7965     if (hashBytes != (unsigned)crSpec->mac_size || padIsBad || 
 7966         PORT_Memcmp(databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->buf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13] + databuf[1][2][3][4][5][8][9][12][13]->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], hash, crSpec->mac_size) != 0) {
 7967         /* must not hold spec lock when calling SSL3_SendAlert. */
 7968         ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss);
 7969         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, bad_record_mac);
 7970         /* always log mac error, in case attacker can read server logs. */
 7971         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_BAD_MAC_READ);
 7972 
 7973         SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: mac check d.cpp.dep.html#failed">faileddep.html#failed">[1]dep.html#failed">[2]dep.html#failed">[3]dep.html#failed">[4]dep.html#failed">[5]d.c.dep.html#failed">[6]", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](), ss->fd));
 7974 
 7975         return SECFailure;
 7976     }
 7977 
 7978     ssl3_BumpSequenceNumber(&crSpec->read_seq_num);
 7979 
 7980     ssl_ReleaseSpecReadLock(ss); /*****************************************/
 7981 
 7982     /*
 7983      * The decrypted data is now in databuf.
 7984      *
 7985      * the null decompression routine is right here
 7986      */
 7987 
 7988     /*
 7989     ** Having completed the decompression, check the length again. 
 7990     */
 7991     if (isTLS && databuf->len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > (MAX_FRAGMENT_LENGTH + 1024)) {
 7992         SSL3_SendAlert(ss, alert_fatal, record_overflow);
 7993         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_RECORD_TOO_LONG);
 7994         return SECFailure;
 7995     }
 7996 
 7997     /* Application data records are processed by the caller of this
 7998     ** function, not by this function.
 7999     */
 8000     if (rType == content_application_data) {
 8001             return SECSuccess;
 8002     }
 8003 
 8004     /* It's a record that must be handled by ssl itself, not the application.
 8005     */
 8006 process_it:
 8007     /* XXX  Get the xmit lock here.  Odds are very high that we'll be xmiting
 8008      * data ang getting the xmit lock here prevents deadlocks.
 8009      */
 8010     ssl_GetSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 8011 
 8012     /* All the functions called in this switch MUST set error code if
 8013     ** they return SECFailure or SECWouldBlock.
 8014     */
 8015     switch (rType) {
 8016     case content_change_cipher_spec:
 8017         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleChangeCipherSpecs(ss, databuf);
 8018         break;
 8019     case content_alert:
 8020         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleAlert(ss, databuf);
 8021         break;
 8022     case content_handshake:
 8023         rv[1] = ssl3_HandleHandshake(ss, databuf);
 8024         break;
 8025     /*
 8026     case content_application_data is handled before this switch
 8027     */
 8028     default:
 8029         SSL_DBG(("%d: SSL3[%d]: bogus content type=%d",
 8030                  SSL_GETPID[4](), ss->fd, cText->type));
 8031         /* XXX Send an alert ???  */
 8032         PORT_SetError(SSL_ERROR_RX_UNKNOWN_RECORD_TYPE);
 8033         rv[1] = SECFailure;
 8034         break;
 8035     }
 8036 
 8037     ssl_ReleaseSSL3HandshakeLock(ss);
 8038     return rv[1];
 8039 
 8040 }
 8041 
 8042 /*
 8043  * Initialization functions
 8044  */
 8045 
 8046 /* Called from ssl3_InitState, immediately below. */
 8047 /* Caller must hold the SpecWriteLock. */
 8048 static void
 8049 ssl3_InitCipherSpec(sslSocket *ss, ssl3CipherSpec *spec)
 8050 {
 8051     spec->cipher_def               = &bulk_cipher_defs[cipher_null];
 8052     PORT_Assert[1](spec->cipher_def->cipher == cipher_null);
 8053     spec->mac_def                  = &mac_defs[mac_null];
 8054     PORT_Assert[1](spec->mac_def->mac == mac_null);
 8055     spec->encode                   = Null_Cipher;
 8056     spec->decode[1]                   = Null_Cipher;
 8057     spec->destroy                  = NULL;
 8058     spec->mac_size                 = 0;
 8059     spec->master_secret            = NULL;
 8060     spec->bypassCiphers            = PR_FALSE;
 8061 
 8062     spec->msItem.data[2]              = NULL;
 8063     spec->msItem.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]               = 0;
 8064 
 8065     spec->client.write_key         = NULL;
 8066     spec->client.write_mac_key     = NULL;
 8067     spec->client.write_mac_context = NULL;
 8068 
 8069     spec->server.write_key         = NULL;
 8070     spec->server.write_mac_key     = NULL;
 8071     spec->server.write_mac_context = NULL;
 8072 
 8073     spec->write_seq_num.high       = 0;
 8074     spec->write_seq_num.low        = 0;
 8075 
 8076     spec->read_seq_num.high        = 0;
 8077     spec->read_seq_num.low         = 0;
 8078 
 8079     spec->version[2][3]                  = ss->opt.enableTLS
 8080                                           ? SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_1_TLS
 8081                                           : SSL_LIBRARY_VERSION_3_0;
 8082 }
 8083 
 8084 /* Called from:        ssl3_SendRecord
 8085 **                ssl3_StartHandshakeHash() <- ssl2_BeginClientHandshake()
 8086 **                ssl3_SendClientHello()
 8087 **                ssl3_HandleServerHello()
 8088 **                ssl3_HandleClientHello()
 8089 **                ssl3_HandleV2ClientHello()
 8090 **                ssl3_HandleRecord()
 8091 **
 8092 ** This function should perhaps acquire and release the SpecWriteLock.
 8093 **
 8094 **
 8095 */
 8096 static SECStatus
 8097 ssl3_InitState(sslSocket *ss)
 8098 {
 8099     PK11Context *md5[1]  = NULL;
 8100     PK11Context *sha  = NULL;
 8101     SECStatus    rv[1];
 8102     PORT_Assert[1]( ss->opt.noLocks || ssl_HaveSSL3HandshakeLock(ss));
 8103 
 8104     if (ss->ssl3.initialized)
 8105             return SECSuccess;        /* Function should be idempotent */
 8106 
 8107     ss->ssl3.policy = SSL_ALLOWED;
 8108 
 8109     ssl_GetSpecWriteLock(ss);
 8110     ss->ssl3.crSpec = ss->ssl3.cwSpec = &ss->ssl3.specs[0];
 8111     ss->ssl3.prSpec = ss->ssl3.pwSpec = &ss->ssl3.specs[1];
 8112     ss->ssl3.hs.rehandshake = PR_FALSE;
 8113     ssl3_InitCipherSpec(ss, ss->ssl3.crSpec);
 8114     ssl3_InitCipherSpec(ss, ss->ssl3.prSpec);
 8115 
 8116     ss->ssl3.hs.ws = (ss->sec.isServer) ? wait_client_hello : wait_server_hello;
 8117 #ifdef NSS_ENABLE_ECC
 8118     ss->ssl3.hs.negotiatedECCurves = SSL3_SUPPORTED_CURVES_MASK;
 8119 #endif
 8120     ssl_ReleaseSpecWriteLock(ss);
 8121 
 8122     /*
 8123      * note: We should probably lookup an SSL3 slot for these
 8124      * handshake hashes in hopes that we wind up with the same slots
 8125      * that the master secret will wind up in ...
 8126      */
 8127     SSL_TRC(30,("%d: SSL3[%d]: d/beos/btime.c.dep.html#start">startd/zlib/deflate.c.dep.html#start">[1]d/zlib/inffast.c.dep.html#start">[2] handshake hashes", d/selfserv/selfserv.c.dep.html#SSL_GETPID">SSL_GETPIDdep.html#SSL_GETPID">[4](), ss->fd));
 8128     if (ss->opt.bypassPKCS11[1]) {
 8129         MD5_Begin((MD5Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.md5_cx);
 8130         SHA1_Begin((SHA1Context *)ss->ssl3.hs.sha_cx);
 8131     } else {
 8132         ss->ssl3.hs.md5[1] = md5[1] = PK11_CreateDigestContext(SEC_OID_MD5);
 8133         if (md5[1] == NULL) {
 8134             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MD5_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 8135             goto loser;
 8136         }
 8137         rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.md5[1]);
 8138         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 8139             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_MD5_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 8140             goto loser;
 8141         }
 8142 
 8143         sha = ss->ssl3.hs.sha = PK11_CreateDigestContext(SEC_OID_SHA1);
 8144         if (sha == NULL) {
 8145             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SHA_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 8146             goto loser;
 8147         }
 8148         rv[1] = PK11_DigestBegin(ss->ssl3.hs.sha);
 8149         if (rv[1] != rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess) {
 8150             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SSL_ERROR_SHA_DIGEST_FAILURE);
 8151             goto loser;
 8152         }
 8153     }
 8154 
 8155     ss->ssl3.initialized = PR_TRUE;
 8156 
 8157     return SECSuccess;
 8158 
 8159 loser:
 8160     if (md5[1] != NULL) PK11_DestroyContext(md5[1], PR_TRUE);
 8161     if (sha != NULL) PK11_DestroyContext(sha, PR_TRUE);
 8162     return SECFailure;
 8163 }
 8164 
 8165 /* Returns a reference counted object that contains a key pair.
 8166  * Or NULL on failure.  Initial ref count is 1.
 8167  * Uses the keys in the pair as input.
 8168  */
 8169 ssl3KeyPair *
 8170 ssl3_NewKeyPair( SECKEYPrivateKey * privKey, SECKEYPublicKey * pubKey)
 8171 {
 8172     ssl3KeyPair * pair;
 8173 
 8174     if (!privKey || !pubKey) {
 8175         PORT_SetError(PR_INVALID_ARGUMENT_ERROR);
 8176             return NULL;
 8177     }
 8178     pair = PORT_ZNew(ssl3KeyPair);
 8179     if (!pair)
 8180             return NULL;                        /* error code is set. */
 8181     pair->refCount = 1;
 8182     pair->privKey  = privKey;
 8183     pair->pubKey   = pubKey;
 8184     return pair;                        /* success */
 8185 }
 8186 
 8187 ssl3KeyPair *
 8188 ssl3_GetKeyPairRef(ssl3KeyPair * keyPair)
 8189 {
 8190     PR_AtomicIncrement(&keyPair->refCount);
 8191     return keyPair;
 8192 }
 8193 
 8194 void
 8195 ssl3_FreeKeyPair(ssl3KeyPair * keyPair)
 8196 {
 8197     PRInt32 newCount =  PR_AtomicDecrement(&keyPair->refCount);
 8198     if (!newCount) {
 8199         if (keyPair->privKey)
 8200             SECKEY_DestroyPrivateKey(keyPair->privKey);
 8201         if (keyPair->pubKey)
 8202             SECKEY_DestroyPublicKey( keyPair->pubKey);
 8203             PORT_Free(keyPair);
 8204     }
 8205 }

 8209 /*
 8210  * Creates the public and private RSA keys for SSL Step down.
 8211  * Called from SSL_ConfigSecureServer in sslsecur.c
 8212  */
 8213 SECStatus
 8214 ssl3_CreateRSAStepDownKeys(sslSocket *ss)
 8215 {
 8216     SECStatus             rv[1]           = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 8217     SECKEYPrivateKey *    privKey;                /* RSA step down key */
 8218     SECKEYPublicKey *     pubKey;                /* RSA step down key */
 8219 
 8220     if (ss->stepDownKeyPair)
 8221         ssl3_FreeKeyPair(ss->stepDownKeyPair);
 8222     ss->stepDownKeyPair = NULL;
 8223 #ifndef HACKED_EXPORT_SERVER
 8224     /* Sigh, should have a get key strength call for private keys */
 8225     if (PK11_GetPrivateModulusLen(ss->serverCerts[kt_rsa].SERVERKEY) >
 8226                                                      EXPORT_RSA_KEY_LENGTH) {
 8227         /* need to ask for the key size in bits */
 8228         privKey = SECKEY_CreateRSAPrivateKey(EXPORT_RSA_KEY_LENGTH * BPB[1][2],
 8229                                              &pubKey, NULL);
 8230             if (!privKey || !pubKey ||
 8231             !(ss->stepDownKeyPair = ssl3_NewKeyPair(privKey, pubKey))) {
 8232             ssl_MapLowLevelError(SEC_ERROR_KEYGEN_FAIL);
 8233             rv[1] = SECFailure;
 8234         }
 8235     }
 8236 #endif
 8237     return rv[1];
 8238 }

 8240 
 8241 /* record the export policy for this cipher suite */
 8242 SECStatus
 8243 ssl3_SetPolicy(ssl3CipherSuite which, int policy)
 8244 {
 8245     ssl3CipherSuiteCfg *suite;
 8246 
 8247     suite = ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg(which, cipherSuites[1][2]);
 8248     if (suite == NULL) {
 8249         return SECFailure; /* err code was set by ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg */
 8250     }
 8251     suite->policy = policy;
 8252 
 8253     if (policy == SSL_RESTRICTED) {
 8254         ssl3_global_policy_some_restricted[1] = PR_TRUE;
 8255     }
 8256 
 8257     return SECSuccess;
 8258 }
 8259 
 8260 SECStatus
 8261 ssl3_GetPolicy(ssl3CipherSuite which, PRInt32 *oPolicy)
 8262 {
 8263     ssl3CipherSuiteCfg *suite;
 8264     PRInt32             policy;
 8265     SECStatus           rv[1];
 8266 
 8267     suite = ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg(which, cipherSuites[1][2]);
 8268     if (suite) {
 8269             policy = suite->policy;
 8270         rv[1]     = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 8271     } else {
 8272             policy = SSL_NOT_ALLOWED;
 8273         rv[1]     = SECFailure;        /* err code was set by Lookup. */
 8274     }
 8275     *oPolicy = policy;
 8276     return rv[1];
 8277 }

 8279 /* record the user preference for this suite */
 8280 SECStatus
 8281 ssl3_CipherPrefSetDefault(ssl3CipherSuite which, PRBool enabled)
 8282 {
 8283     ssl3CipherSuiteCfg *suite;
 8284 
 8285     suite = ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg(which, cipherSuites[1][2]);
 8286     if (suite == NULL) {
 8287         return SECFailure; /* err code was set by ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg */
 8288     }
 8289     suite->enabled = enabled;
 8290     return SECSuccess;
 8291 }
 8292 
 8293 /* return the user preference for this suite */
 8294 SECStatus
 8295 ssl3_CipherPrefGetDefault(ssl3CipherSuite which, PRBool *enabled)
 8296 {
 8297     ssl3CipherSuiteCfg *suite;
 8298     PRBool              pref;
 8299     SECStatus           rv[1];
 8300 
 8301     suite = ssl_LookupCipherSuiteCfg(which, cipherSuites[1][2]);
 8302     if (suite) {
 8303             pref   = suite->enabled;
 8304         rv[1]     = rv[1]/selfserv[1].c.dep.html#SECSuccess">SECSuccess;
 8305     } else {
 8306             pref   = SSL_NOT_ALLOWED;
 8307         rv[1]     = SECFailure;        /* err code was set by Lookup. */
 8308     }
 8309     *enabled = pref;
 8310     return rv[1];
 8311 }
